01:43.336 --> 01:45.772
NARRATOR: Michelle Payne
was just six months old

01:45.772 --> 01:48.741
when her mother Mary
died in a car accident,

01:48.741 --> 01:52.812
leaving her father, Paddy,
a single dad to ten children

01:52.812 --> 01:56.850
ranging in age from 16
to a tiny baby.

01:56.850 --> 02:00.687
PADDY: She was being breastfed
when her mother was killed,

02:00.687 --> 02:02.422
and, uh, that was a worry.

02:02.422 --> 02:06.893
But she came through it good,
took the bottle straightaway.

02:06.993 --> 02:12.499
MICHELLE: I think all the kids helped out and it wasn't too bad.

02:12.699 --> 02:16.736
Bernadette used to look
after me. [CHUCKLES]

02:17.470 --> 02:18.905
Stevie and I
were the little kids,

02:18.905 --> 02:22.041
so we'd always get left out
most of the time,

02:22.041 --> 02:23.843
but we still had a lot of fun.

02:23.843 --> 02:27.614
NARRATOR: The bond between
Stevie and his little sister

02:27.614 --> 02:28.715
was plain to see.

02:28.715 --> 02:31.484
MICHELLE: Growing up
in a family of ten kids

02:31.484 --> 02:33.253
is like you would imagine.

02:33.253 --> 02:34.287
Without our mum in our lives,

02:34.287 --> 02:36.990
it was just crazy,
hectic as anything.

02:36.990 --> 02:38.725
Everybody had to work
at the stables.

02:38.725 --> 02:40.693
It was just like
everybody had their set chores

02:40.693 --> 02:43.696
and we all had to work.
That was just the way it was.

02:43.696 --> 02:47.000
NARRATOR: Eight of Paddy's
ten children became jockeys.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.068
INTERVIEWER: What do you find
the hardest part?

02:49.068 --> 02:50.470
MICHELLE: Probably keeping
my weight down.

02:50.470 --> 02:53.606
- INTERVIEWER: Were you always going to be a jockey?
- Yep.

02:53.606 --> 02:56.009
INTERVIEWER: Did you ever think
of doing anything else?

02:56.009 --> 02:59.145
Um... no, not at all. [CHUCKLES]

03:01.881 --> 03:04.184
INTERVIEWER: What sort
of jockey would you like to be?

03:04.184 --> 03:07.587
I just want to win
the Melbourne Cup.

03:15.895 --> 03:18.865
[HORSE NICKERING]

03:18.865 --> 03:24.837
[♪♪]

03:44.791 --> 03:49.329
Mum, Bridge, stay with me.

03:52.165 --> 03:53.766
Stay with me.

03:55.668 --> 03:56.803
[EXHALES]

03:56.803 --> 03:59.072
[WHISPERS] That's a good boy.

03:59.072 --> 04:00.873
He's a good boy.

04:00.873 --> 04:03.076
[HORSE SNORTS]

04:05.311 --> 04:08.181
[HORSE WHINNIES]

04:14.821 --> 04:17.290
- [GATE OPENS]
- [CROWD ROARS]

04:17.290 --> 04:20.192
[HOOVES THUDDING]

04:35.174 --> 04:38.945
[CONGREGATION SINGING
"HERE I AM, LORD"]

04:39.245 --> 04:43.216
CONGREGATION:
♪ Here I am, Lord ♪

04:43.216 --> 04:48.955
♪ Is it I, Lord?
I have heard you calling... ♪

04:48.955 --> 04:50.957
BERNADETTE: Come on. We're late.

04:50.957 --> 04:54.127
Come on, Stevie.
Come on, Michelle.

04:54.827 --> 04:59.132
♪ I will go, Lord ♪

04:59.132 --> 05:03.102
♪ If you lead me ♪

05:03.403 --> 05:05.705
♪ I will hold ♪

05:05.705 --> 05:11.177
♪ Your people in my heart. ♪

05:14.614 --> 05:16.516
Lord, we pray,

05:16.516 --> 05:19.786
- that through faith, we will survive all trials...
- [GIGGLES]

05:19.786 --> 05:23.022
...in the full knowledge
of your resurrection.

05:23.022 --> 05:24.023
[FARTING SOUND]

05:24.023 --> 05:24.891
THERESE: That's disgusting!

05:24.891 --> 05:26.526
- PRIEST: Prayer is our path to hope.
- THERESE: Such a pig.

05:26.526 --> 05:31.097
- PATRICK: ...dealt it!
- PRIEST: If we truly believe, then miracles can happen.

05:31.097 --> 05:33.633
Like a long shot
in race six at Randwick

05:33.633 --> 05:37.103
getting up and paying at 40/1,
as it did last Saturday.

05:37.103 --> 05:39.072
- [CONGREGATION LAUGHING]
- God be praised!

05:39.072 --> 05:41.808
CATHY: And it's Canny Boy
in with a chance

05:41.808 --> 05:42.608
moving up the straight.

05:42.608 --> 05:46.212
But now it's Let's Elope
coming up on the inside.

05:46.212 --> 05:48.314
- Let's Elope has spotted the gap--
- Faster!

05:48.314 --> 05:50.516
...and is making a break
from Canny Boy,

05:50.516 --> 05:54.020
who doesn't seem to be able
to handle the weight.

05:54.020 --> 05:54.987
- PATRICK: Get up!
- Wait!

05:54.987 --> 05:59.192
From out of nowhere,
Canny Boy pulls herself up out of the mud--

05:59.192 --> 05:59.926
MAN: Come on, Canny Boy!

05:59.926 --> 06:02.095
...and makes
one last desperate move!

06:02.095 --> 06:05.198
- [BELL RINGS]
- Food's up!

06:05.198 --> 06:06.699
Yay!

06:07.867 --> 06:11.003
- I told you, no whips.
- Since when?

06:11.471 --> 06:12.805
Need some help, bud?

06:12.805 --> 06:15.208
PADDY: Come on, little boy!

06:15.942 --> 06:17.343
Pudding!

06:17.343 --> 06:20.313
Oh, Therese, the salad! Wilbur!

06:20.580 --> 06:22.415
- BERNADETTE: All right, lunch is up!
- This took three hours!

06:22.415 --> 06:24.417
BERNADETTE: Can you please
sit at the table?

06:24.417 --> 06:27.687
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

06:31.924 --> 06:33.359
[CRACKER SNAPS]

06:34.026 --> 06:35.795
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

06:41.834 --> 06:43.903
MARGARET: Guys? Shh, shh.

06:43.903 --> 06:44.871
Bless us, O Lord...

06:44.871 --> 06:47.473
ALL: ...for these, thy gifts,
which we're about to receive.

06:47.473 --> 06:51.544
May the Lord make us
truly thankful. Amen.

06:51.544 --> 06:53.646
BRIGID: Four wins, I've had
for Ginger Hern.

06:53.646 --> 06:56.983
The moment Sapphire Rose gets
Group 2, I'm off for a bloke.

06:56.983 --> 07:00.753
- Can't we say something, Dad?
- It's not my place, Brigid.

07:00.753 --> 07:01.621
You just keep doing the work

07:01.621 --> 07:03.356
and I'm sure Ginger will
give you a ride eventually.

07:03.356 --> 07:04.757
Yeah, work twice as hard
and get half the rides.

07:04.757 --> 07:07.727
- BRIGID: Exactly, it's not fair!
- MICHELLE: Dad, Patrick's eating potatoes.

07:07.727 --> 07:10.329
Come on, son.
It's not worth the risk.

07:10.329 --> 07:11.564
J. Pender will be there
tomorrow.

07:11.564 --> 07:13.633
- He'll be looking for a lightweight.
- Dad!

07:13.633 --> 07:15.301
I'm a lightweight.
He's never asked me.

07:15.301 --> 07:17.236
But, Dad, Brigid is better
than Patrick.

07:17.236 --> 07:20.973
- PATRICK: Thanks a lot, Stinky.
- ANDREW: Dad, Steadfast Lad,

07:20.973 --> 07:22.642
too randy to run straight.

07:22.642 --> 07:23.743
Just rub some Vicks on his nose.

07:23.743 --> 07:26.145
If he can't smell the fillies,
he'll be right.

07:26.145 --> 07:27.713
Should try that on Andrew.

07:27.713 --> 07:29.348
[ALL EXCLAIM]

07:29.348 --> 07:31.417
- PATRICK: Oh, yeah, take that!
- ANDREW: Oh!

07:31.417 --> 07:33.953
[RACE COMMENTARY PLAYS
IN EARPHONE]

07:33.953 --> 07:36.456
[ROWDY CONVERSATION]

07:37.757 --> 07:40.226
MAN: [ON TV] Well, that horse
is gonna be a champion.

07:40.226 --> 07:42.295
Well, can't anyone
understand that?

07:42.295 --> 07:43.329
He's gonna be a champion!

07:43.329 --> 07:46.466
- Can't anyone understand that?
- A champion!

07:46.466 --> 07:49.335
- [ALL SHOUT AND LAUGH]
- ANDREW: Cut it out! Cut it out!

07:49.969 --> 07:51.270
[ALL GASP]

07:51.270 --> 07:52.839
THERESE: [GASPS] There it is!

07:52.839 --> 07:54.040
Shelly ate the plum pudding!

07:54.040 --> 07:55.475
Leave me alone!
Stevie did it too!

07:55.475 --> 07:59.078
Stevie's got Down's syndrome.
You should know better.

07:59.078 --> 07:59.579
Yeah!

07:59.579 --> 08:02.348
ANDREW: Come on, smelly Shelly.
You're up next.

08:02.348 --> 08:03.850
Stop it. She's on kitchen duty.

08:03.850 --> 08:05.351
- ANDREW: Come on.
- It's Cathy's turn!

08:05.351 --> 08:06.652
- It is not!
- ANDREW: Gloves on, Stinky.

08:06.652 --> 08:08.621
It's your turn, Michelle.
I've done the schedule.

08:08.621 --> 08:11.123
- Your turn, your turn!
- Stop pulling my hair!

08:11.123 --> 08:14.060
- Just let go of me!
- PATRICK: Just let go!

08:14.060 --> 08:17.930
You can all go get stuffed!

08:17.930 --> 08:21.334
[ALL LAUGHING]

08:33.145 --> 08:35.081
Where are you going
with that?

08:35.081 --> 08:37.216
I'm going to dig up Mum.

08:40.419 --> 08:43.688
Well, you won't find her
out there, little girl.

08:44.290 --> 08:48.661
If Mum was here, she'd stop
them pulling my hair.

08:50.429 --> 08:52.331
Well, she is here.

08:56.035 --> 08:58.604
She's up there looking after us.

08:59.038 --> 09:00.873
Is she an angel?

09:01.807 --> 09:03.543
You bet she is.

09:05.044 --> 09:08.080
She was when
she was alive as well.

09:12.718 --> 09:14.720
Wish I could see her.

09:15.788 --> 09:17.723
Yeah, that'd be good.

09:29.268 --> 09:31.871
Melbourne Cup, 1965?

09:32.405 --> 09:34.173
Light Fingers.

09:35.207 --> 09:36.008
Jockey?

09:36.008 --> 09:38.511
The Professor. Roy Higgins.

09:39.745 --> 09:42.915
1988?

09:42.915 --> 09:44.717
Empire Rose.

09:46.285 --> 09:47.920
1974?

09:48.321 --> 09:49.956
Think Big?

09:52.425 --> 09:55.728
I reckon those horses will be
getting hungry now.

09:57.330 --> 09:57.863
Colors?

09:57.863 --> 10:01.233
MICHELLE: Green and yellow
stripes with red sleeves.

10:01.233 --> 10:02.835
PADDY: Yeah.

10:03.336 --> 10:05.204
MICHELLE:
God bless Dad and Brigid,

10:05.204 --> 10:08.274
Margaret, Patrick,
Therese, Bernadette,

10:08.274 --> 10:12.745
God bless Maree and Cathy,
and even Andrew.

10:12.745 --> 10:17.683
God bless Wilbur,
and all the horses, and Mum.

10:17.984 --> 10:19.785
Amen!

10:25.725 --> 10:27.693
[STEVIE SNORES]

10:43.776 --> 10:46.445
[HORSE WHINNIES]

11:14.674 --> 11:17.510
PADDY: Not bad. Once again.

11:44.270 --> 11:46.639
Come on, come on!
You're going to be a champion!

11:46.639 --> 11:50.710
MARGARET: Okay,
Black Elastic has been scratched from race six.

11:50.710 --> 11:51.644
THERESE:
I carved a T in it, see?

11:51.644 --> 11:54.280
BERNADETTE: That's not a T.
It doesn't even look like a T. It's a B.

11:54.280 --> 11:57.249
- THERESE: Don't you know your alphabet?
- That's mine. B for Brigid.

11:57.249 --> 11:58.818
Hey, that's Therese's! Brigid!

11:58.818 --> 12:01.053
Can't anyone ever sleep in
in this house? [GROANS]

12:01.053 --> 12:02.922
BERNADETTE: I can't believe
she just took it like that.

12:02.922 --> 12:04.924
Yeah, I'm taking her helmet
for that.

12:04.924 --> 12:05.991
Why are you in the sick chair?

12:05.991 --> 12:08.461
Patrick moved when I was trying
to punch him. Ankle's swollen.

12:08.461 --> 12:10.796
- Can't even get my boot on.
- PADDY: Give it here.

12:10.796 --> 12:12.331
BERNADETTE:
"Can't even get my boot on."

12:12.331 --> 12:15.000
- Don't be such a sook, Andrew.
- THERESE: Watch this.

12:15.000 --> 12:15.501
Ow!

12:15.501 --> 12:16.869
MARGARET: Can you go
help Patrick load the horses?

12:16.869 --> 12:21.006
- BERNADETTE: Why can't Maree help?
- MAREE: I've got a broken arm.

12:21.073 --> 12:23.576
ANDREW: There's no way
I can ride.

12:23.743 --> 12:25.511
Hold that, little girl.

12:26.445 --> 12:28.214
Foot in the air.

12:29.081 --> 12:31.150
Put this in there.

12:33.152 --> 12:35.154
[PADDY AND ANDREW GRUNT]

12:36.455 --> 12:37.990
[PEELS TAPE]

12:40.793 --> 12:43.596
Good as gold. Okay.

12:43.596 --> 12:45.698
Righto, load up!

12:45.698 --> 12:47.333
In the back.

12:47.500 --> 12:49.368
Come on, boy.

12:50.770 --> 12:53.272
[CHILDREN ARGUING
INDISTINCTLY]

12:53.272 --> 12:54.807
PADDY: Shut up.

12:54.940 --> 12:55.841
[SHOUTS] Shut up!

12:55.841 --> 12:57.076
ANNOUNCER:
It's history at Ballarat today.

12:57.076 --> 13:00.913
Five of the Payne family siblings will be taking part in race four.

13:00.913 --> 13:02.948
A Guinness Book of Records
moment.

13:02.948 --> 13:06.652
So, the field is set,
and they're off!

13:07.453 --> 13:08.921
How are they doing, little girl?

13:08.921 --> 13:10.189
Therese is in front.

13:10.189 --> 13:11.791
It's too early. I told her.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.192
What about the others?

13:13.192 --> 13:14.927
- Brigid's fourth.
- PADDY: Patrick?

13:14.927 --> 13:16.695
- Seventh.
- Smart boy.

13:16.695 --> 13:18.898
Could hear your girls
screaming at each other

13:18.898 --> 13:20.800
from the other side
of the track, Paddy.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.201
Wouldn't be my girls, Joanie.

13:22.201 --> 13:25.070
[LAUGHS] I got you two
an ice cream.

13:25.070 --> 13:26.806
Andrew's coming last.

13:26.806 --> 13:27.740
Good for Andrew.

13:27.740 --> 13:29.642
They're bunched tight
on the turn.

13:29.642 --> 13:30.609
JOANIE: Shelly...

13:30.609 --> 13:31.944
PADDY: They'll drift out
somewhere round the 400.

13:31.944 --> 13:34.814
- Shelly, ice-cream.
- Therese is dropping back.

13:34.814 --> 13:38.350
- Brigid?
- MICHELLE: She's moved to the outside.

13:38.350 --> 13:40.186
Go, Brigid!

13:40.186 --> 13:41.854
[CROWD CHEERS AND SHOUTS]

13:41.854 --> 13:43.856
- Brigid, right?
- MICHELLE: By a length.

13:43.856 --> 13:46.258
Then Patrick.
Therese come third.

13:46.258 --> 13:47.626
Andrew come last.

13:47.626 --> 13:50.062
Well, I hope
J. Pender was watching.

13:50.062 --> 13:51.096
A few more races like that,

13:51.096 --> 13:54.433
and Patrick will get a run
at the Melbourne Cup.

13:54.433 --> 13:55.568
But Brigid won.

13:55.568 --> 13:59.338
Girls don't ride
the Melbourne Cup.

14:03.008 --> 14:04.243
PADDY: I'll make you a cuppa.

14:04.243 --> 14:06.111
- No. I can't have anything.
- Listen.

14:06.111 --> 14:10.616
Every jockey feels like this
before the Melbourne Cup.

14:10.616 --> 14:12.685
PATRICK: But the odds
are so long.

14:12.685 --> 14:14.086
It's just gambling.

14:14.086 --> 14:15.754
It's nothing to do with
riding a horse.

14:15.754 --> 14:21.193
The only thing that matters
is the odds you give yourself.

14:23.729 --> 14:26.899
[CAR APPROACHES, BRAKES]

14:31.103 --> 14:33.606
I've got my money on you.

14:34.340 --> 14:35.875
Oh, thanks.

14:39.445 --> 14:41.814
[CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

14:43.249 --> 14:47.253
[CAR REVERSES OUT]

14:50.489 --> 14:52.391
[CHILDREN SHOUT EXCITEDLY]

14:52.391 --> 14:55.561
Hang on! No, no!
Careful, careful! Careful!

14:55.561 --> 14:57.930
ANNOUNCER: [ON TV]
And there's an air of excitemet

14:57.930 --> 14:59.031
before the 1991 Melbourne Cup.

14:59.031 --> 15:02.534
Australia's most important
race card about to begin.

15:02.534 --> 15:04.336
All set to go for
the Melbourne Cup.

15:04.336 --> 15:06.972
Stand by for the race
that stops the nation.

15:06.972 --> 15:09.074
The light's on. Away and racing!

15:09.074 --> 15:11.277
- [ALL SHOUT AND CHEER]
- Go, Patrick!

15:11.277 --> 15:13.178
WOMAN:
Oh, Patrick's out in front!

15:13.178 --> 15:16.081
- MICHELLE: Go, Patrick!
- WOMAN: Come on, Patrick!

15:16.081 --> 15:18.384
Go, Sunshine Sally!

15:18.617 --> 15:20.753
Oh. No, up, up, up, up.

15:20.753 --> 15:22.288
Right. Go right.

15:22.288 --> 15:24.089
Yes! That's it! Perfect!

15:24.323 --> 15:26.625
MICHELLE: Come on, Patrick!

15:27.192 --> 15:29.895
Go, Patrick! Go!

15:30.095 --> 15:31.697
Go, Patrick! Let her go!

15:31.697 --> 15:33.265
ANNOUNCER:
Here comes Super Impose.

15:33.265 --> 15:35.367
At the 200, Let's Elope
races to the lead...

15:35.367 --> 15:37.303
WOMAN: Oh, he's fallen
right behind!

15:37.303 --> 15:38.704
Shiva's Revenge is late.

15:38.704 --> 15:40.539
But Let's Elope bolted
in the Melbourne Cup!

15:40.539 --> 15:42.408
Shiva's Revenge,
a Cummings quinella!

15:42.408 --> 15:44.777
- Third, Magnolia Hall and then-
- [BELL RINGS]

15:44.777 --> 15:47.313
Patrick come last.

15:47.413 --> 15:49.248
PADDY: Yep.

15:52.151 --> 15:55.487
How can a horse
that was winning come last?

15:55.487 --> 16:00.359
PADDY: Because he went fast
at the wrong end of the race.

16:03.295 --> 16:06.732
Yep. That's the Melbourne Cup.

16:08.000 --> 16:09.635
It's an upside-down race.

16:09.635 --> 16:12.338
Anyway, if you can go
from first to last,

16:12.338 --> 16:15.841
no reason you can't go
from last to first.

16:19.445 --> 16:24.583
["DREAMS" BY THE CRANBERRIES
PLAYING]

16:26.652 --> 16:28.821
- See you. Have a good day.
- See you, bud.

16:28.821 --> 16:32.992
- Bye, Dad. Thanks. Hey, good luck, Cathy.
- CATHY: Thanks.

16:36.328 --> 16:37.830
- GIRL: Stevie!
- [GIRLS GIGGLE]

16:37.830 --> 16:40.632
PADDY: Come on, Stevie.
Stop staring.

16:40.632 --> 16:42.768
[STEVIE GIGGLES]

16:43.836 --> 16:48.540
[♪]

16:51.977 --> 16:54.913
♪ Oh my life ♪

16:54.913 --> 16:57.549
So, it's not that she's falling
behind in her studies, then?

16:57.549 --> 17:00.319
No, Michelle is
an above-average student.

17:00.319 --> 17:01.320
It's just that...

17:01.320 --> 17:03.822
she keeps asking
to be excused from class,

17:03.822 --> 17:05.991
sometimes as often
as four or five times.

17:05.991 --> 17:07.992
Well, she does have
her mum's bladder.

17:07.992 --> 17:12.798
I am concerned that
she may have the bulimia.

17:12.798 --> 17:14.665
The... The what?

17:14.665 --> 17:15.666
It's an eating disorder.

17:15.666 --> 17:18.871
Eating disorder? She's
the only one that does eat!

17:18.871 --> 17:21.040
It is not healthy
to starve yourself.

17:21.040 --> 17:24.843
Sister, I take it
you've never been a jockey?

17:25.877 --> 17:29.248
MICHELLE: [SOFTLY]
Come on. Come on. Come on!

17:29.248 --> 17:31.984
♪ Because it came from you ♪

17:31.984 --> 17:34.420
That's it. That's it!

17:34.420 --> 17:37.122
Yes! Yes!

17:38.123 --> 17:38.590
[GASPS]

17:38.590 --> 17:40.893
What the dickens
is going on here?

17:40.893 --> 17:45.097
I just wanted to see how Brigid
was going at Sandown.

17:46.331 --> 17:49.201
Five Payne girls I've lost,
and all for what?

17:49.201 --> 17:53.806
So they could sit on the back
of a quadruped for $5 an hour?

17:53.806 --> 17:54.973
$6.75.

17:54.973 --> 17:58.444
That's it. You don't have to
follow your sisters.

17:58.444 --> 18:02.681
Commit to your education.
Make your own choice.

18:02.681 --> 18:04.283
♪ Oh my life ♪

18:04.283 --> 18:07.719
♪ Is changing every day ♪

18:07.719 --> 18:09.388
♪ In every possible way ♪

18:09.388 --> 18:12.991
PADDY: [OVER MEGAPHONE]
Pull up. Pull up!

18:14.860 --> 18:17.362
MICHELLE:
What was wrong with that?

18:19.865 --> 18:22.067
PADDY: Your timing's out.

18:22.067 --> 18:22.935
I counted it right.

18:22.935 --> 18:26.338
You're my apprentice.
If I say you're out, you're out!

18:26.338 --> 18:31.577
Now, six at evens,
last two furlongs at 12.

18:31.577 --> 18:32.377
MICHELLE: Okay.

18:32.377 --> 18:37.049
In your head, "One monkey,
two monkeys, three monkeys."

18:37.049 --> 18:40.519
MICHELLE: [WHISPERS] Four monkeys,
five monkeys, six monkeys...

18:40.519 --> 18:43.522
PADDY: Always walk the track
before you race,

18:43.522 --> 18:44.523
but between races,

18:44.523 --> 18:46.725
not when it's looking like
a bowling green.

18:46.725 --> 18:48.494
And memorize
where the divots are.

18:48.494 --> 18:51.530
There's no point
after they've filled them in.

18:51.797 --> 18:53.632
Now, feel it.

18:55.434 --> 18:57.636
How much moisture's in it?

18:57.636 --> 18:59.238
It's damp.

18:59.304 --> 19:01.240
What about over there?

19:11.617 --> 19:13.752
- Harder.
- PADDY: Which means?

19:13.752 --> 19:15.454
- Faster.
- Good.

19:15.454 --> 19:18.524
So, no matter
what barrier you draw,

19:18.524 --> 19:21.360
you want to get to
the hardest part of the course,

19:21.360 --> 19:23.162
quick as you can.

19:23.662 --> 19:25.531
How you race...

19:26.732 --> 19:28.600
is written in there.

19:33.405 --> 19:35.307
Come on, little girl.

19:36.275 --> 19:40.579
A horse gallops with his lungs,
he perseveres with his heart

19:40.579 --> 19:42.581
and he wins with his character.

19:46.318 --> 19:51.657
PADDY: It's not just about speed.
It's about patience.

19:51.657 --> 19:55.394
You're all bunched in,
you can't breathe,

19:55.394 --> 19:57.029
you think it's all done,

19:57.029 --> 20:02.668
and then the horses all start
fatiguing at different times.

20:02.668 --> 20:06.071
And suddenly, a gap opens.

20:06.071 --> 20:07.406
And that's God talking to you.

20:07.406 --> 20:10.209
And you'd better listen to God,
because he will close that gap

20:10.209 --> 20:13.612
quicker than you can say
your mother's name.

20:19.484 --> 20:22.888
[THROUGH MEGAPHONE]
You're riding slow. Pick it up.

20:23.555 --> 20:26.525
Use your knees. Use your hands.

20:27.526 --> 20:31.230
If you don't take the gap,
they'll say you're a coward,

20:31.230 --> 20:32.431
because you're a girl.

20:32.431 --> 20:34.099
It's all about strength.

20:34.099 --> 20:37.135
You've got to keep enough petrol
in the tank for the last 100.

20:37.135 --> 20:40.405
It's not about strength.
It's about positioning.

20:40.405 --> 20:41.974
Okay?
You don't rely on the whip.

20:41.974 --> 20:44.743
You push up the neck
with the heel of your hands.

20:44.743 --> 20:46.411
And if you take the gap
and lose,

20:46.411 --> 20:49.548
they'll say you're reckless
and lacking in technique,

20:49.548 --> 20:51.483
because you're a girl.

20:52.484 --> 20:54.052
PADDY: Good!

20:58.257 --> 21:01.159
Finally, you're listening to me!

21:12.337 --> 21:14.072
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

21:14.072 --> 21:17.676
- Yours is over there, love.
- No girls in here.

21:31.590 --> 21:34.126
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

21:36.328 --> 21:37.763
MAN: Love.

21:38.263 --> 21:39.831
You're in here.

21:55.080 --> 21:57.182
PADDY: Now, remember
what I taught you.

21:57.182 --> 22:00.118
Wait till they fan,
look for the gap.

22:00.118 --> 22:03.288
That's where
you'll win or lose the race.

22:07.793 --> 22:09.194
You good?

22:16.201 --> 22:18.203
Michelle come last, Dad.

22:19.137 --> 22:20.405
Thanks, Steve.

22:20.405 --> 22:22.574
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

22:24.176 --> 22:26.411
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING, CHEERING]

22:26.411 --> 22:28.113
MAN: Keep going!

22:28.580 --> 22:31.416
[CROWD CLAMORING INDISTINCTLY]

22:33.852 --> 22:36.154
STEVIE: Michelle come last, Dad.

22:36.521 --> 22:37.989
Yeah, I noticed that, Stevie.

22:37.989 --> 22:40.659
STEVIE: [CALLS OUT]
She come last, Dad!

22:40.659 --> 22:42.294
Yep.

22:42.861 --> 22:45.330
Get out of there, Michelle!

22:51.436 --> 22:53.905
Don't say it, Stevie.

22:56.775 --> 22:59.277
- Want a pie?
- Yes, please.

22:59.277 --> 23:00.645
Come on.

23:03.715 --> 23:05.117
MICHELLE: I saw the gap.

23:05.117 --> 23:06.718
How come you didn't take it?

23:06.718 --> 23:08.653
[SIGHS] I couldn't.

23:08.653 --> 23:12.090
The gap was moving faster
than my horse.

23:13.125 --> 23:16.061
PADDY: Maybe you just
don't have it in you.

23:19.231 --> 23:23.301
I think we could give your old
school a call tomorrow.

23:23.301 --> 23:29.241
Yeah. Might have to repeat the
school year, but, you know...

23:36.515 --> 23:38.183
["FIGHT LIKE A GIRL"
BY WILSN PLAYING]

23:38.183 --> 23:41.119
♪ You can knock me down ♪

23:41.119 --> 23:45.657
♪ But I know
I will stand back up ♪

23:45.657 --> 23:46.858
♪ Mm ♪

23:46.858 --> 23:50.162
♪ You can tell me
what I can't do ♪

23:50.162 --> 23:55.133
♪ But you know
I'mma call your bluff ♪

23:55.133 --> 23:56.301
♪ Mm, yeah ♪

23:56.301 --> 23:59.504
♪ I don't care
What you think I need ♪

23:59.504 --> 24:02.741
♪ I'll never be
What you want me to be... ♪

24:02.741 --> 24:05.544
- MAN: Clear!
- ANNOUNCER: Stand by.

24:05.544 --> 24:08.447
♪ I'm gonna fight like a girl ♪

24:08.447 --> 24:11.116
♪ Gonna take on the world ♪

24:11.116 --> 24:13.985
♪ With this fire in my soul ♪

24:13.985 --> 24:14.786
♪ Oh ♪

24:14.786 --> 24:17.189
♪ Run for the diamonds
And gold ♪

24:17.189 --> 24:21.393
♪ I'm making my own way,
Own way ♪

24:21.393 --> 24:23.695
♪ And I'm never gonna break ♪

24:23.695 --> 24:27.165
♪ Oh, I... ♪

24:27.165 --> 24:30.402
PADDY: It's not just
about speed.

24:30.635 --> 24:32.103
It's about patience.

24:32.103 --> 24:35.140
ANNOUNCER: She gets the upper
hand and draws away.

24:35.140 --> 24:38.210
A big moment
for Michelle Payne.

24:38.210 --> 24:41.413
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

24:43.615 --> 24:46.685
ANNOUNCER: Michelle kicks off
her career in great style.

24:46.685 --> 24:48.119
MAN: Good on ya, Shelly!
Top ride, love!

24:48.119 --> 24:52.657
ANNOUNCER: So the dynasty that is the Payne clan continues.

24:52.657 --> 24:56.228
Remarkably, an eighth
Payne sibling jockey

24:56.228 --> 24:58.296
comes back a winner.

25:00.131 --> 25:01.666
Brigid.

25:02.501 --> 25:04.369
She's had a fall.

25:06.805 --> 25:08.673
PADDY: [TEARFULLY] Our Brigid.

25:08.673 --> 25:12.010
Our... beloved daughter...
[CLEARS THROAT]

25:12.010 --> 25:16.248
sister and jockey.

25:16.748 --> 25:20.252
She was just the second woman
in the state

25:20.252 --> 25:22.320
to ride professionally.

25:22.320 --> 25:26.825
She didn't just
break down barriers.

25:26.825 --> 25:29.761
She knocked them
right over. [SOBS]

25:38.970 --> 25:41.139
She's with her mother now.

26:21.112 --> 26:23.181
PADDY: Hi, little girl.

26:23.915 --> 26:25.584
You go good?

26:25.884 --> 26:28.386
Yeah. I won.

26:52.911 --> 26:54.579
I want to ride with Ginge.

26:54.579 --> 26:59.317
No way. You've still got a year
of your apprenticeship to go.

27:01.820 --> 27:04.990
You let the others ride with
different trainers. Why can't I?

27:04.990 --> 27:07.292
Because you're not ready!

27:09.194 --> 27:11.029
I'm ready.

27:11.029 --> 27:14.299
PADDY: You're ready
when I say you are!

27:14.633 --> 27:16.267
I'm ready, Dad.

27:16.267 --> 27:18.870
I'm lucky if I get
a ride a month.

27:18.870 --> 27:22.841
You've only got Chattanooga
and Percival's Pride left, Dad.

27:22.841 --> 27:25.143
How am I supposed
to get race-fit

27:25.143 --> 27:27.379
when you've only got two horses?

27:27.946 --> 27:32.250
Patience, little girl.
You just need more time.

27:32.250 --> 27:34.119
[SIGHS]

27:42.494 --> 27:44.663
I've been patient for two years.

27:44.663 --> 27:46.331
You could have a fine career
in the country.

27:46.331 --> 27:48.299
I don't want a fine career
in the bloody country!

27:48.299 --> 27:51.736
I want to ride Group 1s.
I want to be the best.

27:51.736 --> 27:53.171
No!

27:54.372 --> 27:57.475
How long do I have to wait for?

27:57.475 --> 27:59.444
Till I'm dead?

28:01.012 --> 28:04.315
You will do as I say,
little girl!

28:05.617 --> 28:07.919
I'm not your little girl.

28:45.490 --> 28:47.525
[ENGINE STARTS]

29:40.812 --> 29:42.747
Hi. I'm Michelle Payne.

29:42.747 --> 29:46.851
Uh, I'm a jockey.
I'm available for track work.

29:50.455 --> 29:53.424
I'll just be outside
if anyone needs me.

29:56.861 --> 30:00.165
[MEN CHATTER
INDISTINCTLY]

30:05.937 --> 30:07.205
How'd she run?

30:07.205 --> 30:08.807
JOCKEY: Yeah, clean in the wind,

30:08.807 --> 30:10.742
big, strong action
on the straight.

30:10.742 --> 30:14.479
All right, well,
take her round again. Easy.

30:16.681 --> 30:18.583
Another Payne, eh?

30:20.084 --> 30:20.585
Yeah!

30:20.585 --> 30:22.253
Is that tap ever gonna
be turned off?

30:22.253 --> 30:26.457
Oh, I'm still an apprentice,
but I'm happy to ride--

30:26.457 --> 30:28.159
How's your dad?

30:28.159 --> 30:30.528
Good! Yeah. Yeah, good.

30:30.528 --> 30:32.530
Say g'day to him for me.

30:32.530 --> 30:35.867
MAN: You reckon she'll be ready
by Saturday, mate?

30:36.367 --> 30:39.070
See you get him
stretched out a little.

30:51.783 --> 30:53.818
[SIGHS]

30:58.756 --> 31:01.259
[ALARM RINGS]

31:01.326 --> 31:03.795
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

31:10.869 --> 31:11.970
- Ollie.
- Ollie.

31:11.970 --> 31:14.639
- Hey, fellas.
- G'day, son.

31:16.307 --> 31:18.376
- [CHEERING]
- D. Oliver!

31:19.811 --> 31:20.612
Ah, the great man.

31:20.612 --> 31:21.846
- How are you?
- How are you?

31:21.846 --> 31:24.182
- Ollie, how are you, son?
- Good, good.

31:24.182 --> 31:26.284
[CHATTER CONTINUES]

31:35.226 --> 31:36.127
[BELL TOLLS]

31:36.127 --> 31:39.397
JOAN: How's Shelly going
in the big smoke?

31:39.397 --> 31:42.433
PADDY: Well, Cathy says
she's struggling.

31:42.433 --> 31:43.401
Therese tells me--

31:43.401 --> 31:45.169
Hang on, why are
Cathy and Therese

31:45.169 --> 31:47.605
telling you about
your own daughter?

31:47.605 --> 31:48.806
Joanie... [CLEARS THROAT]

31:48.806 --> 31:52.343
I think she might need someone
to manage her down there.

31:52.343 --> 31:55.813
If you're looking at me, I've
never managed anyone in my life.

31:55.813 --> 32:00.151
See, all the others, they...
they had their time with Mary,

32:00.151 --> 32:04.722
but Michelle,
she's never had any, um...

32:04.722 --> 32:05.690
Mothering?

32:05.690 --> 32:09.861
Someone more than a manager.
Someone to look out for her.

32:09.861 --> 32:11.896
More of a...

32:12.230 --> 32:13.898
female type.

32:14.532 --> 32:17.268
Suppose that roughly sums me up.

32:17.435 --> 32:18.703
Yeah.

32:18.703 --> 32:20.371
I know you won't give me
a race ride yet,

32:20.371 --> 32:24.442
but, um... I'm happy
just to do track work.

32:24.442 --> 32:26.244
You don't even need to pay me.

32:26.244 --> 32:27.412
WOMAN: Thanks, Garry.

32:27.412 --> 32:30.114
Your brother Patrick's
going well as a trainer.

32:30.114 --> 32:31.115
Yeah, he is.

32:31.115 --> 32:33.718
And Andrew's
moved into training too?

32:33.718 --> 32:34.819
Yeah, he has.

32:34.819 --> 32:37.121
You as good as your sisters?

32:37.221 --> 32:37.822
Better.

32:37.822 --> 32:40.091
So, will you give me a ride
or not?

32:40.091 --> 32:42.493
That depends on whether
you give me one.

32:42.493 --> 32:44.796
["I SAID HI" BY AMY SHARK]

32:46.364 --> 32:47.265
[SIGHS]

32:47.265 --> 32:50.335
♪ I stand in the corner
Like a tired boxer ♪

32:50.335 --> 32:53.638
♪ One hand on my cheekbone,
One hand on the rope ♪

32:53.638 --> 32:56.541
♪ And all my veins
Pump blood into my throat ♪

32:56.541 --> 33:00.211
♪ So I can hit the note,
Go do it all again ♪

33:00.211 --> 33:03.381
♪ Tell 'em all I said hi ♪

33:06.818 --> 33:09.654
♪ Tell 'em all I said hi... ♪

33:09.654 --> 33:12.590
How'd you go today? Any luck?

33:12.590 --> 33:16.728
Yeah, good.
Got a couple of possibilities.

33:16.728 --> 33:19.030
CATHY: Yeah. Thanks, Dad.

33:19.030 --> 33:21.566
No, I know.
I'm over the moon. Yeah.

33:21.566 --> 33:24.802
Hey, Michelle just walked in.
I'll hand you over.

33:25.636 --> 33:28.639
Okay. Okay.

33:30.441 --> 33:31.809
Bye, Dad.

33:33.344 --> 33:36.047
Said he had to go
feed the horses.

33:37.982 --> 33:39.117
Yeah.

33:39.117 --> 33:40.485
So, Kerrin and I have
some news...

33:40.485 --> 33:42.954
Do you reckon you could
introduce me to Lee Freedman?

33:42.954 --> 33:45.623
[LAUGHS]
I told you she'd do this.

33:45.623 --> 33:47.091
What?

33:49.127 --> 33:51.029
I'm retiring.

33:51.095 --> 33:52.397
MICHELLE: Why?

33:52.397 --> 33:55.533
CATHY: [LAUGHS] Kerrin and I
are getting married!

33:55.900 --> 33:58.169
No, why are you retiring?

33:58.169 --> 34:00.405
Because I've had
over 3,000 rides

34:00.405 --> 34:01.706
and there's other things
I want to do

34:01.706 --> 34:05.643
than get up at 3 a.m. and ride
round and round in circles.

34:07.045 --> 34:09.080
Cong-- Congratulations!

34:09.080 --> 34:11.181
- Thank you!
- Thanks.

34:13.184 --> 34:15.620
[♪]

34:18.156 --> 34:19.322
Wombat!

34:19.322 --> 34:20.992
WOMBAT: What?

34:20.992 --> 34:23.428
Bairdy wants me
to take him out again.

34:23.428 --> 34:25.463
Really? Well, he never told me.

34:25.463 --> 34:27.665
Yeah. Give us a leg up.

34:34.472 --> 34:37.507
Who's that riding
your horse, Bairdy?

34:37.507 --> 34:39.677
No bloody idea.

34:40.911 --> 34:43.047
It's the Payne girl.

34:44.014 --> 34:46.117
BAIRDY: Not bad form.

34:46.117 --> 34:48.786
Hard to tell
with her jodhpurs on.

34:52.456 --> 34:54.425
♪ Tell 'em all I said hi. ♪

34:54.425 --> 34:57.762
JOAN: Yes, she's got
great balance in the saddle.

34:57.762 --> 35:00.098
Yes. "She".

35:00.731 --> 35:04.569
It is a female name
for a good reason, Clive.

35:04.569 --> 35:06.904
A woman jockey.

35:07.205 --> 35:08.906
No, we've covered that, Rusty.

35:08.906 --> 35:14.712
Yeah, female.
A human mare, if you like.

35:14.712 --> 35:17.515
No, Andrew's a trainer now.

35:18.082 --> 35:19.016
Nathan?

35:19.016 --> 35:22.987
Okay, I'm not gonna argue, Nate.
Your loss.

35:25.022 --> 35:26.157
[SIGHS]

35:26.157 --> 35:29.393
Dad asked you to be
my manager, didn't he?

35:29.393 --> 35:31.295
No. I offered.

35:31.762 --> 35:34.932
Okay, yes, he did, but I'm not
supposed to tell you.

35:34.932 --> 35:40.505
And, yes, I have no experience,
and clearly I'm no good at it.

35:40.505 --> 35:42.673
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

35:43.541 --> 35:45.076
Yes?

35:45.309 --> 35:46.611
Oh. Hello, Colin.

35:46.611 --> 35:50.948
Gee, I don't know.
She's pretty busy.

35:50.948 --> 35:54.752
Yeah, look, we should be able
to make that work.

35:55.119 --> 35:59.357
Okay. She'll be there. Bye.

35:59.357 --> 36:01.459
And we're off and racing!
[LAUGHS]

36:01.459 --> 36:05.796
JOANIE: No, Mick,
Werribee's gonna be too tight for her to get to.

36:05.796 --> 36:08.466
MICHELLE: No, it's not.
Kyneton 11:20,

36:08.466 --> 36:09.901
Kyabram... See, 2:10...

36:09.901 --> 36:12.803
- Hands on the wheel.
- And back to Werribee at four o'clock. It's fine.

36:12.803 --> 36:16.574
Oh, dear Jesus, Shelly.
Pull over. Let me drive.

36:16.574 --> 36:17.575
I'll call you back.

36:17.575 --> 36:20.144
["PLEASURE AND PAIN"
BY DIVINYLS PLAYING]

36:20.144 --> 36:20.811
Sorry!

36:20.811 --> 36:23.281
♪ Sooner or later,
I'll find my place ♪

36:23.281 --> 36:26.684
♪ Find my body
better fix my face ♪

36:26.684 --> 36:30.688
♪ Please don't ask me
How I've been getting off ♪

36:30.688 --> 36:32.290
[ALARM BEEPS]

36:33.925 --> 36:37.128
♪ No, please don't ask me ♪

36:37.128 --> 36:40.264
♪ How I've been getting off ♪

36:40.865 --> 36:44.235
♪ It's a fine line
Between pleasure and pain ♪

36:44.235 --> 36:47.638
♪ You've done it once,
You can do it again ♪

36:47.638 --> 36:50.808
♪ Whatever you've done,
Don't try to explain ♪

36:50.808 --> 36:56.881
♪ It's a fine, fine line
between pleasure and pain ♪

36:56.881 --> 36:59.550
Think that'll show
under the dress?

37:00.151 --> 37:03.621
Unless I get a Group 1,
my career's going nowhere.

37:03.621 --> 37:04.689
You need to call
the owners directly.

37:04.689 --> 37:08.492
Shelly, it's my one day off.
I'm trying to get an outfit organized

37:08.492 --> 37:11.128
for your sister's wedding.
Please.

37:11.929 --> 37:16.100
"Weapon of Mass Reduction"?
Now we're talking!

37:16.834 --> 37:19.170
Have you called your father yet?

37:20.204 --> 37:20.671
I tried.

37:20.671 --> 37:23.741
Well, please try harder. You're
both as stubborn as each other.

37:23.741 --> 37:26.744
"Slims, shapes and sculpts".

37:26.744 --> 37:29.313
What am I, the Venus de Milo?

37:29.313 --> 37:32.283
I have tried twice.
He hasn't even tried at all.

37:32.283 --> 37:35.386
Twice! Really? That hard?

37:35.386 --> 37:37.588
Ooh! You must be exhausted.

37:37.588 --> 37:39.957
[CELLPHONE RINGS, BEEPS]

37:39.957 --> 37:42.460
JOANIE: Hello, Peter.

37:43.728 --> 37:45.396
Oh. Um...

37:45.396 --> 37:49.133
No, I'm afraid
she's solidly booked.

37:50.568 --> 37:53.104
Oh! Oh. H-- Hang on.

37:53.104 --> 37:57.141
No, I might just be able
to squeeze you in...

37:57.141 --> 38:02.513
It'll be tight, but I think
she'll be able to do it.

38:02.613 --> 38:04.115
Excellent. Bye!

38:04.115 --> 38:06.684
- You've got a Group 1.
- Are you for real?

38:06.684 --> 38:10.288
Peter Summers. Krasky.
Moonee Valley!

38:10.288 --> 38:13.424
[BOTH SQUEAL, LAUGH]

38:13.424 --> 38:15.526
- Stevie.
- STEVIE: Hi, Shelly.

38:15.526 --> 38:18.996
Hey. Hey, buddy. Um...

38:19.597 --> 38:23.034
- Is Dad there?
- STEVIE: Yeah, he is.

38:23.267 --> 38:25.169
Do you reckon you could
get him for me?

38:25.169 --> 38:26.137
Okay.

38:26.137 --> 38:28.606
Dad. Michelle's on the phone.

38:29.073 --> 38:31.175
He said he's too busy.

38:32.043 --> 38:33.511
Okay.

38:34.512 --> 38:37.214
Hey, can you tell him
that I got a Group 1?

38:37.214 --> 38:39.350
Okay. [CHORTLES]

38:39.350 --> 38:42.486
- Thanks, bud.
- See ya.

38:47.558 --> 38:52.330
ANNOUNCER: And a big welcome to
Moonee Valley on a major Group 1 day.

38:52.330 --> 38:54.598
The track is in
magnificent condition

38:54.598 --> 38:55.733
and it's rated a good four,

38:55.733 --> 38:58.035
and the rail is in
the true place today...

38:58.035 --> 39:03.307
WOMAN: Oh, hi, Damien, hi!
So excited to meet you!

39:03.774 --> 39:05.109
- You made it!
- Sure did.

39:05.109 --> 39:09.747
- [LAUGHS] Did Dad bring you?
- STEVIE: No. Cathy did.

39:10.214 --> 39:11.749
I put ten bucks on you.

39:11.749 --> 39:13.217
[CHUCKLES] Oh, thanks, buddy!

39:13.217 --> 39:16.487
Fourth place. [GIGGLES]

39:18.289 --> 39:19.690
Damp.

39:20.858 --> 39:22.493
Slow on the rail.

39:25.563 --> 39:28.566
[HORSE SNORTS]

39:33.504 --> 39:35.506
STEVIE: It's okay, boy.

39:40.611 --> 39:43.481
Hey, boy. Just relax.

39:43.481 --> 39:45.149
How you going?

39:47.451 --> 39:49.420
You're a good boy.

39:50.921 --> 39:52.490
Gonna win today.

39:53.023 --> 39:54.592
Good boy.

39:55.760 --> 39:56.527
Hey?

39:56.527 --> 39:59.463
You know that you're not
supposed to be in there?

39:59.964 --> 40:01.432
It's okay.

40:01.599 --> 40:03.667
I'm Down syndrome.

40:05.069 --> 40:06.737
You like horses, do you?

40:06.737 --> 40:09.140
Some I do, some I don't.

40:09.140 --> 40:10.908
[LAUGHS]

40:10.975 --> 40:11.742
STEVIE: Easy.

40:11.742 --> 40:14.445
Yeah, some give me
the shits too.

40:14.445 --> 40:16.647
What do you think of this one?

40:17.081 --> 40:18.716
He's lonely.

40:20.384 --> 40:22.653
But I love this horse.

40:23.220 --> 40:24.922
What's your name, mate?

40:24.922 --> 40:25.723
Stevie Payne.

40:25.723 --> 40:28.826
- You Paddy's son?
- STEVIE: Yes, I am.

40:28.826 --> 40:29.960
There's a good boy.

40:29.960 --> 40:31.862
ANNOUNCER:
Left on a pretty good line, to.

40:31.862 --> 40:35.232
Krasky showed
not a great deal of speed...

40:35.232 --> 40:37.435
[JOCKEYS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY]

40:37.435 --> 40:39.904
JOCKEY: Oi! Keep going!

40:41.639 --> 40:46.210
- JOCKEY 1: Get back! What are you doing?
- JOCKEY 2: Get off me!

40:46.210 --> 40:47.845
Coming through!

40:47.845 --> 40:49.380
Inside!

40:49.380 --> 40:52.249
JOCKEY 1: You're bloody on me!
Get off!

40:52.616 --> 40:53.350
Get out of the way!

40:53.350 --> 40:58.122
- MICHELLE: Get off me!
- JOCKEY: Get back to the bush where you belong!

40:59.123 --> 41:01.926
But Michelle Payne is in
the winner's circle tonight,

41:01.926 --> 41:03.828
and she gets Krasky home
by three-quarters.

41:03.828 --> 41:07.431
Eldehara second, ahead of Smooth Crew,
then Twisted Heart,

41:07.431 --> 41:09.266
a gap in the race
in to Princess Tippity...

41:09.266 --> 41:12.837
You should be hauled in front
of the stewards for that.

41:13.003 --> 41:15.573
You put the entire field
in danger.

41:15.573 --> 41:16.907
I put the field in danger?

41:16.907 --> 41:20.044
You're the one in the wrong. You
moved when there was no room.

41:20.044 --> 41:22.646
What do you want me to do?
Roll out the red carpet for you?

41:22.646 --> 41:26.250
MICHELLE: Just remind me who came first and who came second.

41:26.250 --> 41:28.085
Correct weight.

41:29.253 --> 41:31.956
I'm pulling you
from Cranbourne tomorrow.

41:31.956 --> 41:34.091
The wedding's at 1:00.
It's too tight.

41:34.091 --> 41:38.128
No, it's not. No, I've done
the timings. It's fine.

41:38.128 --> 41:39.430
Nice ride out there, Michelle.

41:39.430 --> 41:41.198
- Thanks, Rusty.
- RUSTY: G'day, Joan.

41:41.198 --> 41:43.801
Do you reckon you can get your
weight down to 50 by Saturday?

41:43.801 --> 41:47.505
No, Rusty, she definitely
can't. She's 53 kilos.

41:47.505 --> 41:50.441
- Horse?
- Vladivostok. Sandown.

41:50.441 --> 41:51.475
Group 1.

41:51.475 --> 41:52.610
Sure can.

41:52.610 --> 41:54.512
- Three kilos? No way.
- Easy.

41:54.512 --> 41:57.715
- Great.
- MICHELLE: Thanks.

41:58.916 --> 42:01.852
[♪]

42:45.696 --> 42:49.567
PRIEST: What terrific conditions
we have here today, folks.

42:49.567 --> 42:53.737
We've got a fine young filly
from a great pedigree

42:53.737 --> 42:55.539
and a terrific young stallion.

42:55.539 --> 42:57.942
[ALL LAUGH]

43:01.445 --> 43:04.515
PRIEST: But seriously,
we gather here

43:04.515 --> 43:07.618
to unite these two people
in matrimony.

43:07.618 --> 43:11.722
Their decision to marry
has not been taken lightly,

43:11.722 --> 43:13.724
and today, they publicly declare

43:13.724 --> 43:16.594
their private love and devotion
to each other.

43:16.594 --> 43:18.329
PADDY: K. McEvoy,
what can I say?

43:18.329 --> 43:22.600
I would thank him for
taking Cathy off my hands,

43:22.600 --> 43:23.801
except look at you, mate.

43:23.801 --> 43:25.703
You're punching
above your weight.

43:25.703 --> 43:27.538
- Oh!
- [ALL LAUGH]

43:27.538 --> 43:28.906
He's a terrific bloke.

43:28.906 --> 43:31.775
Uh, more importantly,
a terrific jockey.

43:31.775 --> 43:33.310
[ALL LAUGH]

43:33.310 --> 43:37.581
PADDY: And a lucky one too,
because he's got our Cathy today,

43:37.581 --> 43:39.750
and, um... like all my girls,

43:39.750 --> 43:43.020
she gets her looks
from her mum, and, um...

43:43.020 --> 43:45.522
we remember her today,
but, um...

43:45.522 --> 43:49.627
Anyway, I want to toast
the bridal couple.

43:49.627 --> 43:51.962
Please raise your glasses.

43:51.962 --> 43:53.631
To K. McEvoy and Cathy.

43:53.631 --> 43:57.034
- The happy couple.
- [ALL CHEER]

43:57.935 --> 43:59.670
[APPLAUSE]

43:59.670 --> 44:02.239
PADDY: And if I could just
take a moment

44:02.239 --> 44:06.110
to toast someone
who has done more work

44:06.110 --> 44:07.878
than anyone else I know

44:07.878 --> 44:13.150
and has finally been
rewarded for that.

44:14.451 --> 44:16.120
Our Stevie...

44:16.120 --> 44:21.792
has last week been offered
a full-time job for D.K. Weir

44:21.792 --> 44:23.527
at his new training outfit
at Warrnambool.

44:23.527 --> 44:25.729
- So, here's to you, Stevie.
- [ALL CHEER]

44:25.729 --> 44:28.732
PADDY: Good on ya, mate.
We're so proud of you, mate.

44:28.732 --> 44:33.203
ALL: [CHANT]
Stevie! Stevie! Stevie!

44:33.203 --> 44:33.937
[CHEERING, APPLAUSE]

44:33.937 --> 44:37.341
[BAND PLAYING "LOVE REALLY HURTS WITHOUT YOU" BY BILLY OCEAN]

44:37.341 --> 44:40.344
[BOTH LAUGH]

44:41.211 --> 44:43.580
I am so proud of you, buddy.

44:43.580 --> 44:44.281
Thanks.

44:44.281 --> 44:47.384
♪ You don't give nothing to me ♪

44:47.384 --> 44:48.485
♪ You painted a smile ♪

44:48.485 --> 44:52.690
♪ And you dress all the while
to excite me ♪

44:53.257 --> 44:55.826
♪ Don't you know
you're turning me on... ♪

44:55.826 --> 44:57.795
- I'm gonna sit down.
- Yeah.

44:57.795 --> 44:59.096
♪ I can't stop... ♪

44:59.096 --> 45:03.167
[BAND PLAYS "FOREVER NOW"
BY COLD CHISEL]

45:13.911 --> 45:16.080
How's it going, Stinky?

45:17.247 --> 45:19.616
Come on. Haven't seen you
eat anything all night.

45:19.616 --> 45:22.052
What weight are you
trying to get to?

45:22.052 --> 45:23.587
50 by tomorrow.

45:23.587 --> 45:26.790
[CHORTLES] Are you nuts?

45:27.024 --> 45:28.525
I'm still two and a half over.

45:28.525 --> 45:30.961
I finally have a chance
to ride a good horse.

45:30.961 --> 45:33.130
I've spent a year
riding all the hacks.

45:33.130 --> 45:35.065
Group 1s always get
pulled off for the blokes.

45:35.065 --> 45:38.669
No, no, no. Every apprentice
gets pulled off rides, Stinky.

45:38.669 --> 45:42.139
I was pulled off,
what, ten times?

45:42.139 --> 45:44.675
[SCOFFS] Try 100!

45:50.347 --> 45:52.216
ANDREW: He'll come 'round,
Shell.

45:52.216 --> 45:53.951
No, he won't.

45:53.951 --> 45:56.120
He's stubborn and selfish.

45:56.120 --> 45:57.621
He only thinks about himself.

45:57.621 --> 46:01.058
Right. So you must
take after Mum, then.

46:01.058 --> 46:05.596
He only ever wanted me to stick around to help him run this place.

46:05.596 --> 46:08.065
You really think that's why?

46:08.165 --> 46:12.703
Maybe he didn't want to lose
another one of his girls.

46:16.607 --> 46:20.110
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

46:23.413 --> 46:25.349
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

46:27.451 --> 46:29.987
[CHEERING CONTINUES]

46:30.888 --> 46:32.422
[CAR HORN TOOTS]

47:04.788 --> 47:06.423
[SIGHS]

48:15.626 --> 48:18.629
[HEATER BLOWS]

48:20.898 --> 48:22.900
[FENCEPOST CRACKS]

48:38.682 --> 48:41.418
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

49:13.650 --> 49:16.286
- [SCALES BEEP]
- MAN: Fifty-two.

49:26.129 --> 49:28.598
- [SCALES BEEP]
- MAN: Fifty.

49:29.766 --> 49:32.970
Correct weight. Good job.
You all right?

49:32.970 --> 49:34.905
- Yeah, good.
- Good.

49:34.905 --> 49:36.139
- [SCALES BEEP]
- MAN: Forty-eight.

49:36.139 --> 49:38.175
ANNOUNCER: So, the last
of them loading in now.

49:38.175 --> 49:41.712
Vladivostok for Michelle Payne
takes her place in the stalls,

49:41.712 --> 49:44.247
and they're ready
in the 1,300 meters.

49:44.247 --> 49:44.848
MAN: Clear!

49:44.848 --> 49:48.318
ANNOUNCER: Starter has them now.
They're set.

49:48.785 --> 49:50.387
Ready to go.

49:50.954 --> 49:51.555
[GATE CLATTERS]

49:51.555 --> 49:54.591
ANNOUNCER: Vladivostok
for Michelle Payne jumps okay.

49:54.591 --> 49:55.826
But doesn't muster early speed.

49:55.826 --> 49:58.228
Space Lab and Future Perfect
first to begin

49:58.228 --> 50:00.797
from Midnight Storm
and The Flag Is Flying.

50:00.797 --> 50:01.898
JOCKEY: Come on,
give us a bit of room!

50:01.898 --> 50:04.935
ANNOUNCER: ...the lead now and settles in front of South Island.

50:04.935 --> 50:06.336
Future Perfect
gets into a good place

50:06.336 --> 50:08.805
ahead of Midnight Storm
and Space Lab, then Realign...

50:08.805 --> 50:11.208
- JOCKEY: Keep going!
- ANNOUNCER: ...Door Fly, behind them...

50:11.208 --> 50:12.876
JOCKEY: Get off me, jockey!

50:12.876 --> 50:15.445
ANNOUNCER: Schumpeter well back
with Generalissimo

50:15.445 --> 50:18.515
and Vladivostok well back
and held up for a run.

50:18.515 --> 50:19.449
Turning in, Butt Out has it.

50:19.449 --> 50:21.885
Tackled by South Island,
Midnight Storm and Future Perfect.

50:21.885 --> 50:24.287
Running on now is Generalissim.
Schumpeter making ground.

50:24.287 --> 50:28.158
Not a lot of room for Vladivostok,
but he is making ground.

50:28.158 --> 50:29.659
In fact, he's charging
through the field.

50:29.659 --> 50:32.329
South Island got to Butt Out
and Future Perfect.

50:32.329 --> 50:33.463
Generalissimo running on.

50:33.463 --> 50:34.931
But Vladivostok
bursts through late,

50:34.931 --> 50:37.901
takes the lead for Michelle
Payne and gets up to win!

50:37.901 --> 50:38.735
[HORSE SQUEALS]

50:38.735 --> 50:43.340
ANNOUNCER: Ooh!
One down after going over the line. Vladivostok there.

50:43.340 --> 50:44.708
[HORSE HUFFS]

50:44.708 --> 50:47.411
[SIREN WAILS]

50:48.678 --> 50:53.850
Vladivostok having a heavy fall
after the winning post.

50:53.850 --> 50:56.820
[HORSE NEIGHS]

51:03.560 --> 51:05.729
[HORSE HUFFS]

51:08.999 --> 51:11.101
[HORSE GROANS]

51:18.742 --> 51:20.710
[HUFFS]

51:22.512 --> 51:23.680
[CROWD CLAMORING]

51:23.680 --> 51:24.948
ANNOUNCER:
The horse is quite okay

51:24.948 --> 51:28.785
and the ambulance attendants
are rushing over

51:28.785 --> 51:32.456
to help out Michelle Payne now.

51:37.694 --> 51:39.262
Dad!

51:39.863 --> 51:42.432
Dad, Dad! She had a fall!

51:42.566 --> 51:44.301
ANNOUNCER: She's not moving.

51:44.301 --> 51:48.004
This looks to be a nasty one
as the ambulance attendants...

51:48.004 --> 51:49.439
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

51:49.439 --> 51:51.942
I know. I know. I'm on my way.

51:51.942 --> 51:52.876
Oh, shit!

51:52.876 --> 51:55.579
Andrew! Michelle's had a fall.

51:56.213 --> 51:59.950
Michelle Payne
still unresponsive.

52:02.552 --> 52:05.489
[HEART MONITOR BEEPS]

52:06.089 --> 52:08.758
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

52:09.025 --> 52:10.293
Tell me she's alive.

52:10.293 --> 52:11.828
- What's the story?
- She in surgery?

52:11.828 --> 52:13.730
- We don't know yet.
- PATRICK: Is it her neck?

52:13.730 --> 52:14.931
Have you heard from Dad yet?

52:14.931 --> 52:16.933
- No. Have you seen him?
- It's okay.

52:16.933 --> 52:18.401
Anyone see her fall?

52:18.401 --> 52:19.536
Where's the doctor? Is he here?

52:19.536 --> 52:21.705
- CATHY: Here's Dad now.
- Who are we speaking to?

52:21.705 --> 52:25.475
- I heard it was bad.
- CATHY: It looked really bad.

52:26.243 --> 52:26.977
PATRICK: Hey, mate.

52:26.977 --> 52:29.212
CATHY: Dad,
they've intubated her and they're trying to stabilize her,

52:29.212 --> 52:31.748
but we don't know
anything else yet.

52:32.115 --> 52:35.652
For the moment, she's better
in a comatose state.

52:35.652 --> 52:37.087
The scans reveal
a lot of bleeding

52:37.087 --> 52:39.990
inside and outside the brain,
and there is some evidence

52:39.990 --> 52:41.725
of damage to the right
frontal lobe.

52:41.725 --> 52:44.961
- What does that mean?
- DOCTOR: It means we wait.

52:44.961 --> 52:47.063
The blood clots
will slowly reabsorb

52:47.063 --> 52:51.034
and we'll be able to assess
the extent of Michelle's damage.

52:51.034 --> 52:53.303
I'm sorry it's not great news.

52:53.303 --> 52:54.404
[SIGHS]

52:54.404 --> 52:57.007
[TRASH CAN CLATTERS NOISILY]

52:59.609 --> 53:01.344
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

53:03.113 --> 53:05.582
[VENTILATOR HISSES]

53:27.037 --> 53:28.638
It's your mum's.

53:34.711 --> 53:37.147
I was selfish, I know that.

53:37.814 --> 53:39.649
But I was right.

53:41.685 --> 53:43.887
If... If...

53:43.887 --> 53:46.456
If only I hadn't let her go.

53:46.456 --> 53:48.325
No, stop kicking yourself,
Paddy.

53:48.325 --> 53:53.430
You've done a grand job
under impossible circumstances.

53:53.863 --> 53:56.633
I've lost two of them, Father.

53:57.801 --> 53:59.903
You're a good man, Paddy.

54:00.837 --> 54:02.672
God sees that.

54:03.473 --> 54:07.377
It's not God's forgiveness
I'm after.

54:07.644 --> 54:11.915
Come on.
Let's pray for her together.

54:12.849 --> 54:17.053
BOTH: Hail Mary, full of grace.
The Lord is with thee.

54:17.053 --> 54:18.688
Blessed art thou among women,

54:18.688 --> 54:22.492
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus...

54:40.644 --> 54:43.280
[COUGHS]

54:46.650 --> 54:48.652
Yeah, much better now.

54:55.692 --> 54:57.193
Hey, Stinky.

55:00.764 --> 55:01.665
Hey?

55:01.665 --> 55:04.234
Why the hell are you
giving her that?

55:04.234 --> 55:05.735
Thought it might cheer her up.

55:05.735 --> 55:07.704
She can't read, you moron.

55:07.971 --> 55:09.005
You know, even if she could,

55:09.005 --> 55:11.508
it's the last thing
she should be reading.

55:11.508 --> 55:13.610
- Coffee?
- Sure.

55:16.746 --> 55:18.481
Okay.

55:19.582 --> 55:20.617
In the second at Doomben,

55:20.617 --> 55:24.654
we've got C. Webb
on Craig-Lee Rubble.

55:24.654 --> 55:27.324
I hear he goes
like the clappers.

55:31.161 --> 55:32.996
NURSE: Ready?

55:32.996 --> 55:34.864
Gently, gently.

55:37.467 --> 55:41.571
THERAPIST: Can you lift
that hand for me, Michelle?

55:43.807 --> 55:45.108
[GRUNTS]

55:46.910 --> 55:48.712
Good girl.

55:49.979 --> 55:51.214
Tell me...

55:51.214 --> 55:54.517
do you remember
how to spell your name?

55:55.285 --> 55:56.886
M...

55:57.987 --> 55:59.522
I...

56:03.660 --> 56:05.261
THERAPIST: That's okay.

56:06.396 --> 56:08.765
How many fingers
am I holding up?

56:14.204 --> 56:15.905
MICHELLE: Th...

56:17.006 --> 56:19.309
THERAPIST: That's enough
for today.

56:20.076 --> 56:21.578
You did really well.

56:21.578 --> 56:23.646
And we'll carry on tomorrow.

56:24.114 --> 56:27.417
Who won the 1983 Melbourne Cup?

56:29.319 --> 56:30.754
Kiwi.

56:31.454 --> 56:32.489
Jockey?

56:32.489 --> 56:35.158
MICHELLE:
Jimmy 'Pumper' Cassidy.

56:35.158 --> 56:36.726
1930?

56:36.726 --> 56:39.362
- MICHELLE: Phar Lap.
- Colors?

56:39.362 --> 56:42.165
Crimson, black-white sleeves.

56:42.499 --> 56:44.234
See, you've got to ask
some questions

56:44.234 --> 56:47.036
that she might at least
be interested in.

57:07.023 --> 57:08.925
PADDY: Righto, Stevie.

57:14.931 --> 57:16.499
All right, mate.

57:16.499 --> 57:18.234
[GRUNTS] Here.

57:18.768 --> 57:20.770
Right, let's have you,
little girl.

57:20.770 --> 57:22.439
[MICHELLE GRUNTS]

57:23.139 --> 57:27.444
- [MICHELLE GRUNTS]
- There you go. Good.

57:28.278 --> 57:29.579
Okay, mate.

57:29.579 --> 57:31.648
Yeah, Andrew made that.

57:41.591 --> 57:43.092
[SIGHS]

58:06.983 --> 58:08.818
[SOFTLY] Shit!

58:10.520 --> 58:13.623
- [FRIDGE DOOR CLOSES]
- MICHELLE: [GROANS]

58:18.428 --> 58:19.896
DOCTOR: Well done.

58:19.896 --> 58:21.965
You've made great progress,
Michelle.

58:21.965 --> 58:24.901
But another injury to the head
could be fatal.

58:24.901 --> 58:28.938
You've got to do
whatever you can to protect it.

58:28.938 --> 58:31.341
When can I ride again?

58:31.341 --> 58:33.810
[CHUCKLES]

58:51.961 --> 58:53.863
[NICKERS]

58:56.199 --> 58:58.601
[HORSE NEIGHS]

59:01.237 --> 59:03.873
MICHELLE: [SOFTLY] Hi.

59:44.447 --> 59:46.115
CATHY: You're out of your mind.

59:46.115 --> 59:48.718
Get married, go travelling
and have kids.

59:48.718 --> 59:49.886
There's a reason they call it

59:49.886 --> 59:51.220
the most dangerous sport
on earth.

59:51.220 --> 59:55.058
- [SIGHS]
- Who'll look after you if you're permanently brain-damaged?

59:55.058 --> 59:57.260
Paralyzed? Dad can't.

59:57.260 --> 59:58.494
I will.

59:58.494 --> 01:00:01.397
JOAN: Shelly, I can't be
part of this anymore.

01:00:01.397 --> 01:00:04.834
If I get you a ride
and something happens...

01:00:04.834 --> 01:00:07.003
So, what do you want me to do?

01:00:07.003 --> 01:00:08.671
Go back to being
the youngest of ten,

01:00:08.671 --> 01:00:10.273
doing as I'm told
by everybody else?

01:00:10.273 --> 01:00:11.975
Like you ever did
what you were told!

01:00:11.975 --> 01:00:15.011
MICHELLE: I don't see you telling your husbands to give up,

01:00:15.011 --> 01:00:18.014
- and they've all been injured.
- CATHY: Dad, please,

01:00:18.014 --> 01:00:19.415
just tell her.

01:00:19.415 --> 01:00:21.651
I did try to do that once.

01:00:22.819 --> 01:00:24.921
Didn't work out so well.

01:00:24.988 --> 01:00:25.922
No.

01:00:25.922 --> 01:00:29.425
If that little girl's
made up her mind...

01:00:29.425 --> 01:00:33.496
there's no-one here or in heaven that can make her change it.

01:00:35.231 --> 01:00:38.835
["ALIVE" BY SIA PLAYING]

01:00:40.570 --> 01:00:45.174
♪ I was born in a thunderstorm ♪

01:00:45.174 --> 01:00:49.178
♪ I grew up overnight ♪

01:00:49.178 --> 01:00:54.017
♪ I played alone,
I played on my own ♪

01:00:54.017 --> 01:00:56.886
♪ I survived ♪

01:00:57.220 --> 01:00:57.987
♪ Hey ♪

01:00:57.987 --> 01:01:02.792
♪ I wanted everything
I never had ♪

01:01:02.792 --> 01:01:06.529
♪ Like the love
that comes with light ♪

01:01:06.529 --> 01:01:07.463
I'll pick you up in a week.

01:01:07.463 --> 01:01:09.999
STEVIE: No.
I'm getting the train home.

01:01:09.999 --> 01:01:11.801
♪ And I hated that ♪

01:01:11.801 --> 01:01:15.438
♪ But I survived ♪

01:01:16.839 --> 01:01:18.641
DARREN: Stevie boy! All good?

01:01:18.641 --> 01:01:21.210
- STEVIE: All good. Yep.
- Right.

01:01:21.210 --> 01:01:23.913
[WHINNIES]

01:01:30.019 --> 01:01:32.355
MICHELLE: Hi, boy.
[CLICKS TONGUE]

01:01:32.355 --> 01:01:34.624
What are you doing in there?

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:39.529
What's going on?

01:01:41.130 --> 01:01:44.100
[SNORTS, STAMPS FOOT]

01:01:44.300 --> 01:01:48.638
What's wrong?
What's wrong, buddy?

01:01:48.838 --> 01:01:51.107
[HORSE NEIGHS]

01:01:51.107 --> 01:01:53.276
DARREN: His name is
Prince of Penzance.

01:01:53.276 --> 01:01:56.646
He's had more medical issues
than you.

01:01:56.646 --> 01:01:58.214
It's a shame
you're out of action.

01:01:58.214 --> 01:02:00.316
Could have taken him for a spin.

01:02:00.316 --> 01:02:01.451
I'm not out of action.

01:02:01.451 --> 01:02:05.188
I'm just on a break.
Doctor's given me a month.

01:02:05.188 --> 01:02:08.357
[LAUGHS] Okay.

01:02:10.026 --> 01:02:11.794
[DOOR OPENS]

01:02:11.794 --> 01:02:15.064
WOMAN: Prince's injury's healing
nicely. I've put it up for you.

01:02:15.064 --> 01:02:17.533
- DARREN: Good. Thanks, darl.
- [DOOR CLOSES]

01:02:17.533 --> 01:02:21.003
DARREN: You can take him down
to the beach if you like.

01:02:52.568 --> 01:02:54.804
[LAUGHS]

01:02:55.371 --> 01:02:59.542
MICHELLE: Beautiful boy!
[LAUGHS]

01:03:24.033 --> 01:03:25.935
We'll see if that
eases the tendon.

01:03:25.935 --> 01:03:28.571
- Where's Stevie?
- MICHELLE: I have to ride that horse.

01:03:28.571 --> 01:03:30.206
That is probably the best horse
I've ever ridden.

01:03:30.206 --> 01:03:33.209
Hey, Dusty, when you've finished
your little beauty treatment,

01:03:33.209 --> 01:03:34.310
take Trident out for a trot

01:03:34.310 --> 01:03:36.245
and see if the hindquarters
are still tight.

01:03:36.245 --> 01:03:37.380
DUSTY: No worries, Mr. Weir.

01:03:37.380 --> 01:03:40.917
"Mister"? Do I look like
a bank manager to you, Mick?

01:03:40.917 --> 01:03:43.586
- Not to me.
- Good.

01:03:43.586 --> 01:03:45.354
MICHELLE: Darren?

01:03:46.122 --> 01:03:46.589
Darren!

01:03:46.589 --> 01:03:48.424
You're still following me,
aren't you?

01:03:48.424 --> 01:03:49.625
I will do whatever it takes.

01:03:49.625 --> 01:03:51.460
I will drive every day
to Warrnambool.

01:03:51.460 --> 01:03:54.764
- DARREN: [SIGHS]
- I have to ride that horse.

01:03:56.332 --> 01:03:57.800
Michelle.

01:03:57.800 --> 01:04:01.404
You've fractured your skull.
Now your back.

01:04:01.404 --> 01:04:04.006
Both your elbows. Your neck.

01:04:04.006 --> 01:04:07.476
Is there any part of you
that's not damaged?

01:04:07.710 --> 01:04:09.545
My ability to win.

01:04:10.279 --> 01:04:13.382
Fine. You can bunk in
with Stevie.

01:04:13.382 --> 01:04:16.385
But... no promises.

01:04:18.187 --> 01:04:21.791
You won't regret it, Mr. Weir!
[LAUGHS]

01:04:21.791 --> 01:04:23.292
You'll regret calling me that.
Don't.

01:04:23.292 --> 01:04:25.995
- DARREN: Don't. Good.
- MICHELLE: Yep.

01:04:25.995 --> 01:04:28.865
MICHELLE: [LAUGHS] Yes!

01:04:30.032 --> 01:04:32.034
STEVIE: You're looking good.

01:04:32.101 --> 01:04:33.803
MICHELLE: That's it, boy.

01:04:33.803 --> 01:04:35.371
Oh, much stronger, Prince.

01:04:35.371 --> 01:04:38.507
- STEVIE: Looking really good.
- MICHELLE: Much better.

01:04:40.710 --> 01:04:44.080
- That's it, boy.
- STEVIE: That's it, boy!

01:04:44.580 --> 01:04:48.484
He's getting better.
Good as new.

01:04:48.751 --> 01:04:51.554
- Good boy.
- MICHELLE: Good boy.

01:04:54.156 --> 01:04:54.757
Whoa!

01:04:54.757 --> 01:04:57.059
Maddy, can you take him down
to the water walker?

01:04:57.059 --> 01:05:00.396
- Put him on for ten minutes.
- MADDY: Yep.

01:05:07.370 --> 01:05:10.706
- DARREN: He looks good.
- MICHELLE: Yeah.

01:05:10.706 --> 01:05:13.142
Let's try him on a short run.

01:05:16.746 --> 01:05:18.247
ANNOUNCER:
...Spirit pulled out, raced up,

01:05:18.247 --> 01:05:21.017
but Prince of Penzance
has beaten off Laid Back Larry!

01:05:21.017 --> 01:05:23.586
Prince of Penzance
and Oregon Spirit.

01:05:23.586 --> 01:05:24.687
Down to the back, 50 to go.

01:05:24.687 --> 01:05:26.789
Prince of Penzance
digs in hard, finds plenty,

01:05:26.789 --> 01:05:30.960
and the Prince gets in by three-quarters of a length to Oregon Spirit!

01:05:30.960 --> 01:05:32.662
In the running,
here comes the Prince.

01:05:32.662 --> 01:05:35.998
He said, "See you later, boys."
He moves up on the outside

01:05:35.998 --> 01:05:39.702
and, in a bonanza performance,
goes home and wins well...

01:05:40.036 --> 01:05:43.406
MAN: You managed him beautifully
in the final 400, Shell.

01:05:43.406 --> 01:05:45.274
He sure runs well for you.

01:05:45.274 --> 01:05:47.410
- Cheers!
- Sure does.

01:05:47.410 --> 01:05:49.111
- Michelle Payne.
- Michelle Payne!

01:05:49.111 --> 01:05:51.380
ANNOUNCER: [ON RADIO] Now looking at the Moonee Valley Cup,

01:05:51.380 --> 01:05:53.382
a qualifying race
for the Melbourne Cup,

01:05:53.382 --> 01:05:54.817
and Opinion is the favorite.

01:05:54.817 --> 01:05:57.486
Prince of Penzance,
Michelle Payne,

01:05:57.486 --> 01:05:58.788
four runs back from a spell.

01:05:58.788 --> 01:06:00.957
He's had his issues
with injuries,

01:06:00.957 --> 01:06:02.024
but he might be a chance here.

01:06:02.024 --> 01:06:03.693
This distance looks
ideal for him.

01:06:03.693 --> 01:06:05.795
Ready to go.
They're off and racing.

01:06:05.795 --> 01:06:08.764
And Opinion jumping well
over on the outside,

01:06:08.764 --> 01:06:09.865
the favorite...

01:06:09.865 --> 01:06:11.000
Opinion got away well,

01:06:11.000 --> 01:06:12.868
and going through
is Black Tycoon

01:06:12.868 --> 01:06:13.836
soon after the start.

01:06:13.836 --> 01:06:15.204
Precedence is now
drifting back.

01:06:15.204 --> 01:06:18.207
Black Tycoon, Au Revoir,
Albonetti are up there

01:06:18.207 --> 01:06:22.044
ahead of Epingle and Le Roi,
who holds the rails.

01:06:22.044 --> 01:06:25.781
[HOOVES THUDDING]

01:06:36.826 --> 01:06:41.630
ANNOUNCER: And on the outside,
Prince of Penzance strikes hard!

01:06:41.630 --> 01:06:44.467
Prince of Penzance draws away
and wins it for Michelle Payne!

01:06:44.467 --> 01:06:46.902
ANNOUNCER: Your attention, please.
There's a protest.

01:06:46.902 --> 01:06:50.072
A protest
on the Moonee Valley Cup...

01:06:50.072 --> 01:06:51.741
Don't antagonize them.

01:06:51.741 --> 01:06:55.644
We need this win if he's gonna
get a run in the Melbourne Cup.

01:06:55.644 --> 01:06:57.546
Just keep your cool.

01:06:57.546 --> 01:07:00.249
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:07:01.384 --> 01:07:03.285
MAN: Come in, riders.

01:07:05.454 --> 01:07:09.692
Clearly, there was insufficient
room for you to take the run.

01:07:09.692 --> 01:07:10.760
There was room when I went.

01:07:10.760 --> 01:07:13.262
The runners ahead of me
shifted position and it closed.

01:07:13.262 --> 01:07:17.299
Michelle, you of all people
should know better

01:07:17.299 --> 01:07:19.568
than to put
other jockeys at risk.

01:07:19.568 --> 01:07:20.536
I didn't.

01:07:20.536 --> 01:07:24.373
Okay, let's... let's have
another look. Bernie?

01:07:24.373 --> 01:07:25.875
[MAN CLEARS THROAT]

01:07:25.875 --> 01:07:27.376
MAN 1: This will tell the story.

01:07:27.376 --> 01:07:28.677
MAN 2: She isn't holding
the line at all.

01:07:28.677 --> 01:07:30.379
- MAN 1: That gap's tight.
- MAN 2: Gutsy.

01:07:30.379 --> 01:07:32.248
She's forced Damien over
so far...

01:07:32.248 --> 01:07:34.016
MAN 1: No, look at her! She's...

01:07:34.016 --> 01:07:34.683
ALL: Ooh!

01:07:34.683 --> 01:07:36.585
STEWARD: You are charged
with careless riding.

01:07:36.585 --> 01:07:40.322
Any jockey worth their salt
would have taken that run!

01:07:40.322 --> 01:07:42.591
STEWARD: Are you telling me
how to do my job?

01:07:42.591 --> 01:07:46.262
No.
No, I'm just saying that...

01:07:46.862 --> 01:07:48.864
the gap was there when I went.

01:07:48.864 --> 01:07:51.167
Just keep your cool.
Keep your cool.

01:07:51.167 --> 01:07:52.935
You're suspended for 20 meets.

01:07:52.935 --> 01:07:55.471
MICHELLE: I did not
cause that fall!

01:07:55.471 --> 01:07:57.940
If that was an appeal...

01:07:58.040 --> 01:08:00.142
- it's denied.
- This is not fair!

01:08:00.142 --> 01:08:02.611
STEWARD: Do you want me
to make it 40 meets?

01:08:02.611 --> 01:08:03.813
I'm taking this to the tribunal.

01:08:03.813 --> 01:08:07.083
Oh, and how many times
have you done that, Michelle?

01:08:07.883 --> 01:08:09.452
Dismissed.

01:08:11.287 --> 01:08:13.255
What about the win?

01:08:16.058 --> 01:08:17.560
Rich?

01:08:18.627 --> 01:08:21.296
[ALL CHEER]

01:08:21.296 --> 01:08:23.365
MAN: Well done, Darren!

01:08:23.365 --> 01:08:25.734
MAN: Congratulations!

01:08:25.734 --> 01:08:28.037
Next stop, Melbourne Cup!

01:08:28.037 --> 01:08:29.572
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:08:29.572 --> 01:08:32.741
I'm sorry, Michelle.
But you are the one that's suspended.

01:08:32.741 --> 01:08:33.341
Not that horse.

01:08:33.341 --> 01:08:36.112
I just qualified him
for the Melbourne Cup.

01:08:36.112 --> 01:08:37.613
So, what do you want me to do?

01:08:37.613 --> 01:08:39.048
Sit him in a paddock
for 20 meets?

01:08:39.048 --> 01:08:42.852
I've been on every one of his
starts. I have had six wins.

01:08:42.852 --> 01:08:46.956
Yeah. It was all you.
Dunno why they pay me.

01:08:46.956 --> 01:08:47.857
STEVIE: Okay, Maddy.

01:08:47.857 --> 01:08:50.526
DARREN: Keep going, Drew.
I'm proud of you.

01:08:50.526 --> 01:08:52.060
Yeah.

01:08:52.328 --> 01:08:55.598
- DARREN: All good, Drew?
- DREW: Yeah.

01:08:55.898 --> 01:08:57.466
STEVIE: See you, Michelle.

01:08:57.466 --> 01:08:59.667
Come on. Close up.

01:09:05.207 --> 01:09:07.309
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

01:09:09.145 --> 01:09:09.645
Hello?

01:09:09.645 --> 01:09:13.082
PADDY: I am not dead yet and I
do not want to be resuscitated.

01:09:13.082 --> 01:09:15.783
If the Lord's will is
that I go, I go.

01:09:15.783 --> 01:09:19.020
So just don't let them
put me under the knife.

01:09:19.020 --> 01:09:19.688
I don't want it.

01:09:19.688 --> 01:09:21.090
Barry over there's crook
as a dog, but I'm--

01:09:21.090 --> 01:09:23.692
ANDREW: Dad, just calm down,
all right? You've had a heart attack.

01:09:23.692 --> 01:09:25.594
I'm all right, aren't I, Nursie?

01:09:25.594 --> 01:09:28.430
If the Lord wants me,
he can have me.

01:09:28.430 --> 01:09:31.500
No, Dad.
The Lord doesn't want you.

01:09:31.500 --> 01:09:33.301
I've lived a full life.

01:09:34.904 --> 01:09:35.638
Well...

01:09:35.638 --> 01:09:40.341
I did want to see you
settled down and happy,

01:09:40.341 --> 01:09:42.144
like your sisters.

01:09:42.978 --> 01:09:44.846
It's okay, Dad.

01:09:45.447 --> 01:09:46.881
I've found the one.

01:09:46.881 --> 01:09:50.618
I just... just hope
he's good enough for you.

01:09:50.618 --> 01:09:52.587
Oh, he is, Dad.

01:09:52.688 --> 01:09:54.657
He's a Prince.

01:09:56.759 --> 01:09:59.161
How many legs has he got?

01:09:59.161 --> 01:10:01.363
[LAUGHS]

01:10:05.668 --> 01:10:08.470
NURSE: Excuse me, guys?
He really does need his rest.

01:10:08.470 --> 01:10:11.173
I'll give you a call
if anything changes.

01:10:11.173 --> 01:10:13.042
See you tomorrow, Dad.

01:10:17.012 --> 01:10:18.781
See you, Dad.

01:10:26.121 --> 01:10:27.723
STEVIE: Michelle?

01:10:28.624 --> 01:10:30.059
MICHELLE: Yeah?

01:10:30.059 --> 01:10:33.829
What will happen
if Dad goes away?

01:10:35.698 --> 01:10:37.633
What will happen with me then?

01:10:37.633 --> 01:10:39.101
I'll look after you, buddy.

01:10:39.101 --> 01:10:41.670
Because you haven't got
a boyfriend.

01:10:41.670 --> 01:10:44.306
[BOTH GIGGLE]

01:10:44.907 --> 01:10:46.542
MICHELLE: [LAUGHS] No!

01:10:46.542 --> 01:10:50.246
No, you dingbat! [LAUGHS]

01:10:50.346 --> 01:10:51.981
No.

01:10:51.981 --> 01:10:54.216
'Cause you're my best friend.

01:10:54.350 --> 01:10:57.720
And... we're gonna build a home,

01:10:57.720 --> 01:10:58.821
and I'll have a ton of horses.

01:10:58.821 --> 01:11:02.458
I'll train 'em up and you'll be
my number one strapper.

01:11:02.458 --> 01:11:05.327
What will happen if you die?

01:11:17.306 --> 01:11:19.775
[PHONE RINGS]

01:11:23.712 --> 01:11:26.315
- Hello?
- THERESE: Michelle?

01:11:26.315 --> 01:11:28.951
Michelle, he's gone.

01:11:32.554 --> 01:11:34.056
[SOBS]

01:11:34.056 --> 01:11:35.491
THERESE: Michelle?

01:11:35.491 --> 01:11:38.661
[THERESE SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

01:11:39.228 --> 01:11:41.297
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:11:44.733 --> 01:11:46.535
[SIGHS]

01:11:51.373 --> 01:11:55.711
Stewards and doctors!
They know stuff-all!

01:11:55.711 --> 01:11:58.180
Go fight for your Prince, love.

01:12:14.496 --> 01:12:16.332
DARREN: She's served
her suspension.

01:12:16.332 --> 01:12:21.537
She was the one that qualified your horse
for the Melbourne Cup by taking risks.

01:12:21.537 --> 01:12:22.538
So why not take one on her?

01:12:22.538 --> 01:12:26.108
We've put thousands into this
broken horse's medical bills.

01:12:26.108 --> 01:12:29.945
- Three bone chip operations.
- Major abdominal surgery.

01:12:29.945 --> 01:12:31.313
Six years old.
It's a miracle he's racing.

01:12:31.313 --> 01:12:34.850
- Exactly.
- This is our last chance to make something back.

01:12:34.850 --> 01:12:36.452
And if he doesn't end up
in the top ten,

01:12:36.452 --> 01:12:37.553
that's money
we'll never see again.

01:12:37.553 --> 01:12:41.690
Face facts
- no woman jockey's even come close to winning the Melbourne Cup.

01:12:41.690 --> 01:12:45.694
It all comes down to strength
in that last 100 meters.

01:12:45.694 --> 01:12:47.229
Bottom line, she's too reckless.

01:12:47.229 --> 01:12:49.732
That's why she got susp--

01:12:52.768 --> 01:12:56.071
You've never had a problem
with me riding Prince.

01:12:56.071 --> 01:12:59.575
And now all of a sudden
you want to replace me.

01:13:00.809 --> 01:13:02.311
Why?

01:13:03.245 --> 01:13:04.913
Shell, it's nothing personal.

01:13:04.913 --> 01:13:07.316
We're just trying to give
the horse his best chance.

01:13:07.316 --> 01:13:11.019
I have ridden him
in almost every race.

01:13:11.086 --> 01:13:14.089
I get that horse and he gets me.

01:13:14.490 --> 01:13:15.090
He's mine.

01:13:15.090 --> 01:13:19.661
The Cup is a hard race.
You need strength.

01:13:19.661 --> 01:13:22.197
I'll tell you what you need.

01:13:22.564 --> 01:13:25.334
You think
it's all about strength.

01:13:25.567 --> 01:13:27.770
It is about
so much more than that.

01:13:27.770 --> 01:13:31.907
You need to understand
your horse.

01:13:31.907 --> 01:13:35.811
You need the skill
to read the field.

01:13:35.811 --> 01:13:37.880
And most of all...

01:13:37.946 --> 01:13:40.616
you need to be patient!

01:13:41.116 --> 01:13:44.420
And if you all think
differently, then...

01:13:45.154 --> 01:13:46.922
well, then...

01:13:47.156 --> 01:13:50.058
you're all a bunch
of bloody idiots!

01:13:56.799 --> 01:14:01.303
Do you want to know how to win
the biggest race in the world?

01:14:03.439 --> 01:14:05.040
Like that.

01:14:09.745 --> 01:14:11.613
Busy Cup Day?

01:14:12.181 --> 01:14:14.082
Are you for real?

01:14:14.516 --> 01:14:16.919
[CHUCKLES] You're on.

01:14:16.919 --> 01:14:18.454
- G'day, Darren.
- Hey, Neil.

01:14:18.454 --> 01:14:22.157
If you get barrier 18,
just put it back.

01:14:22.157 --> 01:14:22.825
Okay.

01:14:22.825 --> 01:14:27.463
Yes. 'Cause no horse
has ever won from 18.

01:14:30.065 --> 01:14:31.300
- Stevie?
- Yep?

01:14:31.300 --> 01:14:33.802
- Where's your tie?
- I don't wear ties.

01:14:33.802 --> 01:14:36.405
- Why?
- I don't like 'em.

01:14:36.405 --> 01:14:38.173
Neither do I.

01:14:38.173 --> 01:14:40.642
All right, you need
to get me one or two, okay?

01:14:40.642 --> 01:14:42.411
STEVIE: Okay.
I'll get number one.

01:14:42.411 --> 01:14:45.914
PRESENTER: [ON TV] And the best strapper in the business,
Stevie Payne,

01:14:45.914 --> 01:14:48.217
is gonna come forward
and pick the barrier.

01:14:48.217 --> 01:14:52.154
Steve told me
he's after barrier one or two.

01:14:52.154 --> 01:14:55.991
- And he's picked barrier one!
- [CHEERING]

01:14:56.992 --> 01:15:00.229
PRESENTER: He has
the magic touch, your brother..

01:15:00.229 --> 01:15:02.197
[SIGHS]

01:15:19.081 --> 01:15:21.350
PADDY: The only thing
that matters

01:15:21.350 --> 01:15:23.852
is the odds you give yourself.

01:15:24.553 --> 01:15:26.388
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

01:15:45.274 --> 01:15:48.076
What do you think
his chances are, Stevie?

01:15:48.076 --> 01:15:50.846
I reckon he'll beat
the lot of 'em!

01:15:51.980 --> 01:15:55.884
Well, in that case...

01:15:55.884 --> 01:15:57.319
I know you don't like them,

01:15:57.319 --> 01:16:01.623
but today, you might have to
make an exception.

01:16:10.532 --> 01:16:12.401
[GIGGLES]

01:16:12.401 --> 01:16:14.036
There we go.

01:16:14.236 --> 01:16:16.071
Load it up.

01:16:25.747 --> 01:16:28.750
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

01:16:30.052 --> 01:16:31.219
MICHELLE: Hi, Therese.

01:16:31.219 --> 01:16:33.889
Yes. Yes, I've eaten.

01:16:34.623 --> 01:16:37.292
Uh, a Berocca and a Coke Zero.

01:16:37.693 --> 01:16:41.597
[LAUGHS] That...
That does so count!

01:16:42.731 --> 01:16:45.100
Okay. Bye.

01:16:45.968 --> 01:16:48.604
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

01:16:49.204 --> 01:16:50.138
Patrick.

01:16:50.138 --> 01:16:52.374
[LAUGHS] Hi.

01:16:52.507 --> 01:16:56.578
Don't go too early.
I know. I got it.

01:16:56.578 --> 01:16:58.847
Thanks. Bye.

01:17:18.734 --> 01:17:20.802
Could you tell me
what the odds are

01:17:20.802 --> 01:17:22.804
on Prince of Penzance, please?

01:17:22.804 --> 01:17:25.874
Ooh. Impossible to one? Nah.

01:17:25.874 --> 01:17:30.779
Female rider, up against
D. Oliver and F. Dettori?

01:17:30.779 --> 01:17:33.315
But, happy to take your money!

01:17:33.315 --> 01:17:36.318
Come on! Come on! Ooh!

01:17:38.553 --> 01:17:42.758
I'd like to place $5 on her
each way, please.

01:17:42.758 --> 01:17:44.192
It's a boy horse, ma'am.

01:17:44.192 --> 01:17:48.230
I know it is.
I'm placing it on the girl.

01:17:48.230 --> 01:17:50.165
Ah. $5 it is.

01:17:50.165 --> 01:17:53.402
Love a woman who
throws caution to the wind.

01:17:53.402 --> 01:17:57.673
Actually, make it ten...
each way.

01:17:57.673 --> 01:18:00.542
No, 20. The win.

01:18:01.576 --> 01:18:03.812
[PUNCHES KEYS]

01:18:06.148 --> 01:18:07.649
Thank you.

01:18:11.153 --> 01:18:12.587
JOANIE: Sister.

01:18:13.755 --> 01:18:14.956
[TYRES SCREECH]

01:18:14.956 --> 01:18:17.192
[SCOOTER BEEPS]

01:18:17.592 --> 01:18:20.095
- Morning, Trevor.
- Good morning, Sister.

01:18:20.095 --> 01:18:22.864
Number 19, Prince of Penzance.

01:18:23.031 --> 01:18:24.533
[COINS CLATTER]

01:18:24.533 --> 01:18:28.303
$148.55. For the win.

01:18:28.303 --> 01:18:30.472
She's one of yours, is she?

01:18:32.674 --> 01:18:33.842
Thanks, Trevor.

01:18:33.842 --> 01:18:35.677
[SCOOTER BEEPING]

01:18:35.677 --> 01:18:38.647
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:18:43.852 --> 01:18:46.354
[SILENCE]

01:18:49.057 --> 01:18:52.427
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:18:56.164 --> 01:18:58.867
[SILENCE]

01:19:05.340 --> 01:19:07.342
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:19:14.382 --> 01:19:17.285
[BUGLE PLAYS FIRST CALL]

01:19:20.856 --> 01:19:24.292
[COMMENTARY PLAYS ON TV]

01:19:31.066 --> 01:19:33.902
[TONE SOUNDS OVER P.A.]

01:19:33.902 --> 01:19:35.504
P.A.: Jockeys to
the mounting yard now.

01:19:35.504 --> 01:19:39.641
All Melbourne Cup jockeys
to the mounting yard.

01:19:47.482 --> 01:19:50.852
[BUGLE PLAYS FIRST CALL]

01:19:55.390 --> 01:19:56.992
ANNOUNCER: [OVER P.A.]
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:19:56.992 --> 01:19:58.527
it's time now
to meet the jockeys

01:19:58.527 --> 01:20:00.695
aiming to write their name
into the record books

01:20:00.695 --> 01:20:05.000
as the winner of the 155th
Emirates Melbourne Cup.

01:20:05.000 --> 01:20:05.901
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

01:20:05.901 --> 01:20:08.203
Number 8, Max Dynamite,
Willie Mullins.

01:20:08.203 --> 01:20:09.037
Ollie!

01:20:09.037 --> 01:20:13.842
Ridden by international star
of the turf, Frankie Dettori.

01:20:13.842 --> 01:20:15.010
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

01:20:15.010 --> 01:20:16.044
Number 13, The Offer,

01:20:16.044 --> 01:20:19.080
the legendary trainer
Gai Waterhouse,

01:20:19.080 --> 01:20:20.816
Damien Oliver!

01:20:20.816 --> 01:20:22.083
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

01:20:22.083 --> 01:20:22.651
Ollie!

01:20:22.651 --> 01:20:24.219
Twenty-three
of the 24 riders are male.

01:20:24.219 --> 01:20:26.988
Just the fifth female
to ride in the race,

01:20:26.988 --> 01:20:29.324
say hello to a young lady,
Michelle Payne--

01:20:29.324 --> 01:20:31.860
- [CHEERING] Come on, Michelle!
- ANNOUNCER: ...Prince of Penzance.

01:20:31.860 --> 01:20:34.396
A girl's never gonna win
the Melbourne Cup, mate.

01:20:34.396 --> 01:20:35.864
Not in my lifetime.

01:20:35.864 --> 01:20:38.333
I could improve those odds.

01:20:39.434 --> 01:20:41.670
ANNOUNCER:
Number 23, Excess Knowledge,

01:20:41.670 --> 01:20:46.141
ridden by the man who won
the 2000 Cup aboard Brew,

01:20:46.141 --> 01:20:47.475
Kerrin McEvoy.

01:20:47.475 --> 01:20:49.411
DARREN:
Don't go too hard too fast.

01:20:49.411 --> 01:20:51.613
You want to be between
8th and 14th.

01:20:51.613 --> 01:20:53.815
On the fence, smothered away.

01:20:53.815 --> 01:20:56.484
Yeah, okay. What are we at?

01:20:56.484 --> 01:20:57.085
Hundred to one.

01:20:57.085 --> 01:20:58.920
You'd be at half that
if you were a bloke.

01:20:58.920 --> 01:21:00.689
Just try and finish
in the top ten.

01:21:00.689 --> 01:21:01.990
- All right?
- MICHELLE: Right.

01:21:01.990 --> 01:21:05.060
- Good luck, Michelle.
- Good luck, Shelly.

01:21:06.127 --> 01:21:08.797
- Hey, sis.
- Good luck, Shell.

01:21:10.799 --> 01:21:12.234
- MAN: Good luck, Kerrin.
- WOMAN: Hey, Kerrin!

01:21:12.234 --> 01:21:13.568
- Hey, good luck out there.
- Hey, Shelly!

01:21:13.568 --> 01:21:16.004
- MAN: Good luck with 18.
- See you on the other side.

01:21:16.004 --> 01:21:16.571
[CHUCKLES]

01:21:16.571 --> 01:21:19.040
- WOMAN: Good luck out there!
- Bye.

01:21:30.285 --> 01:21:33.922
[WHISPERS] Hey, boy! Hey, boy.

01:21:33.989 --> 01:21:36.591
Hey, Prince. Beautiful boy.

01:21:36.591 --> 01:21:39.361
- STEVIE: Nice boy.
- [PRINCE SNORTS]

01:21:40.662 --> 01:21:43.198
- Stevie?
- Yeah?

01:21:44.399 --> 01:21:45.700
Can I do this?

01:21:45.700 --> 01:21:47.502
I know the horse can.

01:21:47.502 --> 01:21:49.671
He's gonna be a champion.

01:21:51.573 --> 01:21:53.341
BOTH: A champion!

01:21:53.341 --> 01:21:55.510
[BOTH GIGGLE]

01:21:56.978 --> 01:21:58.980
[SIGHS]

01:21:59.881 --> 01:22:01.683
Let's do this.

01:22:08.256 --> 01:22:09.724
BRUCE MCAVANEY: [ON TV]
...champion rider.

01:22:09.724 --> 01:22:11.526
So, Ollie, for Gai Waterhouse,
on The Offer.

01:22:11.526 --> 01:22:13.929
SIMON O'DONNELL: Look, I'm sure,
even though Gai is probably

01:22:13.929 --> 01:22:16.197
the most positive person
I've ever met in my life,

01:22:16.197 --> 01:22:18.400
she would have liked the skies
to have opened

01:22:18.400 --> 01:22:20.602
and taken some cut
out of this ground

01:22:20.602 --> 01:22:22.971
and given the horse
his best chance,

01:22:22.971 --> 01:22:24.839
'cause that's where
he's a chance

01:22:24.839 --> 01:22:27.075
of running a place
in the Melbourne Cup

01:22:27.075 --> 01:22:27.876
if the ground's wet.

01:22:27.876 --> 01:22:30.111
- It's not today.
- MCAVANEY: He won the Sydney Cup last year.

01:22:30.111 --> 01:22:33.682
This year's Sydney Cup winner
is Grand Marshal...

01:22:35.550 --> 01:22:38.353
[JOCKEYS SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

01:22:38.353 --> 01:22:41.289
Hey, Ollie, you want me
to stay up with her?

01:22:42.791 --> 01:22:45.393
MAN 1: Riders up the back!
Come on!

01:22:45.393 --> 01:22:47.262
Come a bit closer!

01:22:49.464 --> 01:22:53.068
Go on! Move up again, please!

01:22:53.068 --> 01:22:55.070
Get closer! Thank you!

01:22:55.070 --> 01:22:56.438
MAN 2: Come on.

01:22:56.438 --> 01:22:57.539
[HORSE SNORTS]

01:22:57.539 --> 01:22:59.941
- Good boy.
- MAN 2: In you go. In you go.

01:22:59.941 --> 01:23:02.277
- Good boy.
- MAN 2: Come on.

01:23:04.279 --> 01:23:05.947
That's it.

01:23:06.281 --> 01:23:09.017
MAN 1: We'll have to lock
behind this one.

01:23:09.084 --> 01:23:09.951
Keep coming. Keep coming!

01:23:09.951 --> 01:23:13.588
- MAN 1: All right, a bit further.
- MAN 2: Yeah, locked in.

01:23:15.290 --> 01:23:16.658
MAN 2: Grab her head.
Grab her head.

01:23:16.658 --> 01:23:19.995
Come on, go in.
Come on. Up you get.

01:23:23.498 --> 01:23:25.200
MAN: Hang on. Hang on!

01:23:25.200 --> 01:23:29.004
JOCKEY: Can I have a hand?
Can I have a hand?

01:23:31.406 --> 01:23:33.041
[HUFFS]

01:23:41.983 --> 01:23:46.388
Mum, Brig, stay with me.

01:23:48.490 --> 01:23:50.058
Stay with me.

01:23:52.894 --> 01:23:55.330
[WHISPERS] That's a good boy.

01:23:55.330 --> 01:23:57.699
There's a good boy.

01:24:00.301 --> 01:24:04.272
Make sure you give Max a good
ride, 'cause I'm following you.

01:24:04.672 --> 01:24:07.108
What are you doing
after the race?

01:24:08.977 --> 01:24:10.745
Celebrating.

01:24:12.147 --> 01:24:13.782
MAN: Clear!

01:24:13.848 --> 01:24:14.482
[CROWD CHEERS]

01:24:14.482 --> 01:24:16.584
ANNOUNCER: The Offer jumped
well with Trip to Paris.

01:24:16.584 --> 01:24:20.055
Prince of Penzance missed
the start from the inside gate.

01:24:20.055 --> 01:24:21.790
Who Shot Thebarman
got away nicely

01:24:21.790 --> 01:24:24.292
- from Criterion and Sertorius.
- [CROWD CHEERING]

01:24:24.292 --> 01:24:25.493
ANNOUNCER: Over on the outside,

01:24:25.493 --> 01:24:28.296
and Quest for More
going forward with Big Orange.

01:24:28.296 --> 01:24:29.064
[HOOVES THUDDING]

01:24:29.064 --> 01:24:31.766
ANNOUNCER: ...as they both
go up towards the frontrunners.

01:24:31.766 --> 01:24:34.002
It's a bunched field
at the 2,800,

01:24:34.002 --> 01:24:35.136
joining the course proper.

01:24:35.136 --> 01:24:37.138
And Quest for More led
narrowly from Big Orange,

01:24:37.138 --> 01:24:39.607
Excess Knowledge,
Snow Sky and Criterion.

01:24:39.607 --> 01:24:42.944
Max Dynamite getting back,
and so too is Red Cadeaux,

01:24:42.944 --> 01:24:46.181
Preferment, Who Shot Thebarman
and The United States.

01:24:46.181 --> 01:24:47.115
They're followed by Hartnell.

01:24:47.115 --> 01:24:49.017
Bondi Beach a good way
back in the field.

01:24:49.017 --> 01:24:51.886
Behind them is Hokko Brave
and Almoonquith.

01:24:51.886 --> 01:24:53.621
They're followed by Kingfisher.

01:24:53.621 --> 01:24:55.590
They've settled fully.
Not a lot of pace about.

01:24:55.590 --> 01:24:57.292
- MAN: Come on!
- And the favorite, Fame Game,

01:24:57.292 --> 01:24:59.194
has only four or five
behind him.

01:24:59.194 --> 01:25:00.428
Quest for More
has a narrow lead,

01:25:00.428 --> 01:25:04.265
being pressured on the outside by Excess Knowledge and Big Orange.

01:25:04.265 --> 01:25:06.167
Trip to Paris is up there
with Criterion,

01:25:06.167 --> 01:25:10.171
Grand Marshal and Sertorius,
followed by Our Ivanhowe...

01:25:10.171 --> 01:25:10.772
That's good.

01:25:10.772 --> 01:25:13.575
ANNOUNCER: ...and then followed
by Gust of Wind...

01:25:13.842 --> 01:25:17.412
- [HOOVES THUDDING]
- [ANNOUNCER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:25:23.585 --> 01:25:28.423
ANNOUNCER: ...on the fence,
followed by Trip to Paris, Max Dynamite...

01:25:31.326 --> 01:25:34.596
- Come on! Go, Brett!
- Go, Kerry!

01:25:39.968 --> 01:25:42.971
PADDY: Not yet, not yet.
Not yet.

01:25:42.971 --> 01:25:45.640
Wait for the sweet spot.

01:25:50.545 --> 01:25:52.113
Come on!

01:25:59.187 --> 01:26:03.258
ANNOUNCER: ...to Paris is coming into the race.
Snow Sky's wide out...

01:26:03.258 --> 01:26:05.326
Come on, Stinky,
get out of there!

01:26:05.326 --> 01:26:06.461
Come on, Michelle.
Where are you?

01:26:06.461 --> 01:26:09.898
ANNOUNCER: ...Fame Game and The Offer,
and then Sky Hunter...

01:26:09.898 --> 01:26:10.598
Get out of there!

01:26:10.598 --> 01:26:13.434
ANNOUNCER: ...Big Orange still narrowly from Excess Knowledge.

01:26:13.434 --> 01:26:16.838
Snow Sky a bit wider.
Trip to Paris joining in...

01:26:16.838 --> 01:26:19.073
PADDY: Not yet, not yet...
No! No!

01:26:19.073 --> 01:26:22.443
Now! Take it! Run! Take it!

01:26:22.443 --> 01:26:24.145
PADDY: Suddenly a gap opens.

01:26:24.145 --> 01:26:27.549
That's God talking to you,
and you'd better listen to God,

01:26:27.549 --> 01:26:28.616
because he will close that gap

01:26:28.616 --> 01:26:31.853
quicker than you can say
your mother's name.

01:26:31.853 --> 01:26:34.556
[♪♪]

01:26:40.028 --> 01:26:42.130
- Go!
- Guys?

01:26:42.864 --> 01:26:43.932
You've found it, little girl!

01:26:43.932 --> 01:26:46.401
ANNOUNCER: Criterion trying
to find a way through.

01:26:46.401 --> 01:26:48.469
Round the outside
came Sky Hunter

01:26:48.469 --> 01:26:51.839
and Bondi Beach off the track
is making ground too.

01:26:51.839 --> 01:26:54.275
- Our Ivanhowe...
- Come on, Michelle!

01:26:54.275 --> 01:26:56.344
- Yes! Come on!
- Come on! Let him go!

01:26:56.344 --> 01:26:59.280
ANNOUNCER: ...on the extreme outside with The Offer...

01:26:59.280 --> 01:27:00.415
- Come on!
- Come on!

01:27:00.415 --> 01:27:05.186
ANNOUNCER: Snow Sky joining in
and now Trip to Paris is comin.

01:27:05.186 --> 01:27:07.322
They're followed then
by Who Shot Thebarman.

01:27:07.322 --> 01:27:10.558
Going for a run on the inside
is Our Ivanhowe.

01:27:10.558 --> 01:27:12.093
Coming past the 300 meters,

01:27:12.093 --> 01:27:13.928
Excess Knowledge
with the lead narrowly.

01:27:13.928 --> 01:27:16.931
Here's Prince of Penzance
coming on down the outside.

01:27:16.931 --> 01:27:19.200
Prince of Penzance
for Michelle Payne.

01:27:19.200 --> 01:27:21.803
Now Max Dynamite
starts to charge home.

01:27:21.803 --> 01:27:23.538
Prince of Penzance
from Max Dynamite.

01:27:23.538 --> 01:27:27.342
Prince of Penzance!
It's history at Flemington!

01:27:27.342 --> 01:27:28.977
Michelle Payne!

01:27:29.077 --> 01:27:32.380
[♪]

01:27:35.583 --> 01:27:37.485
[SCREAMS]

01:27:38.519 --> 01:27:39.554
[SHRIEKS]

01:27:39.554 --> 01:27:42.290
- Yeah!
- Yes!

01:27:43.258 --> 01:27:47.061
ANNOUNCER: Michelle Payne has created history at Flemington.

01:27:47.061 --> 01:27:50.465
The first lady to win
the Melbourne Cup!

01:27:50.465 --> 01:27:54.435
[♪]

01:28:03.344 --> 01:28:04.912
Thank you, girls.

01:28:25.700 --> 01:28:28.670
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

01:28:28.770 --> 01:28:32.774
JOCKEY: Michelle! Great ride!

01:28:46.254 --> 01:28:47.588
MCAVANEY: Prince of Penzance,

01:28:47.588 --> 01:28:49.924
a horse that's been dogged
by injury, came back.

01:28:49.924 --> 01:28:51.492
He really got himself
into the Cup

01:28:51.492 --> 01:28:53.494
with that great run
at Moonee Valley.

01:28:53.494 --> 01:28:54.362
And this young lady,

01:28:54.362 --> 01:28:56.964
who's ridden the horse
22 times before today,

01:28:56.964 --> 01:29:00.001
and the best thing possible
in Australian racing

01:29:00.001 --> 01:29:04.105
and nearly the world now,
to the Melbourne Cup.

01:29:04.772 --> 01:29:07.342
[ALL LAUGH]

01:29:11.846 --> 01:29:13.314
Whoo!

01:29:16.451 --> 01:29:20.788
That was a great win.
Great ride. Ten out of ten.

01:29:20.788 --> 01:29:24.025
- Correct weight!
- [CHEERING]

01:29:29.764 --> 01:29:34.402
[♪]

01:29:48.649 --> 01:29:50.818
- Woohoo!
- [ALL CHEER]

01:30:02.630 --> 01:30:04.465
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

01:30:24.719 --> 01:30:25.953
STEVIE: Woohoo!

01:30:25.953 --> 01:30:28.790
- [CAR HORN TOOTS]
- STEVIE: Whoo!

01:30:34.629 --> 01:30:36.731
Woohoo!

01:31:04.826 --> 01:31:08.596
I reckon this one can go...
here.

01:31:15.069 --> 01:31:16.938
You went a bit early.

01:31:16.938 --> 01:31:18.840
Couldn't wait.

01:31:19.907 --> 01:31:21.576
You never could.

01:31:22.577 --> 01:31:25.246
Do you want to give me a hand
getting Andrew's horses

01:31:25.246 --> 01:31:26.981
up from the bottom paddock?

01:31:26.981 --> 01:31:29.817
- Yeah.
- PADDY: Righto.

01:32:19.367 --> 01:32:21.135
MICHELLE: I put in
all the effort I could.

01:32:21.135 --> 01:32:22.703
I galloped him
every gallop he had

01:32:22.703 --> 01:32:24.505
and did everything I could
to stay on him,

01:32:24.505 --> 01:32:26.040
because I thought
he had what it takes

01:32:26.040 --> 01:32:27.942
to run a race
in the Melbourne Cup and, um,

01:32:27.942 --> 01:32:30.244
I just wanted to say that
everyone else can get stuffed,

01:32:30.244 --> 01:32:32.413
'cause they think women
aren't strong enough,

01:32:32.413 --> 01:32:34.615
but we just beat the world.

01:32:40.154 --> 01:32:42.356
MICHELLE: Our family's so blessed to have Stevie

01:32:42.356 --> 01:32:44.225
and to share that experience
with him,

01:32:44.225 --> 01:32:46.360
who we've been
so close our whole lives.

01:32:46.360 --> 01:32:48.462
And it's just funny to think
two little kids

01:32:48.462 --> 01:32:50.965
that used to run around
together, on the main stage

01:32:50.965 --> 01:32:53.668
beating all the horses that
come from around the world,

01:32:53.668 --> 01:32:56.170
is absolutely incredible.

